WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:02:33.319 --> 00:02:35.947

3
00:03:11.758 --> 00:03:13.159
Very good.

4
00:03:13.259 --> 00:03:17.923
Exquisitely worked.
You've created a jewel. my boy.

5
00:03:17.964 --> 00:03:23.231
Perfect for a courtesan or priest
to pluck after supper.

6
00:03:23.269 --> 00:03:26.966
or polish Sundays after mass.

7
00:03:27.006 --> 00:03:28.174
In other words...

8
00:03:28.274 --> 00:03:32.438
this violin will never bear my name.

9
00:03:35.882 --> 00:03:39.648
Put your anger into your work. my boy.

10
00:03:40.086 --> 00:03:43.055
Stay with me and learn.

11
00:03:57.303 --> 00:03:59.897
1 million. 1.600.000.

12
00:03:59.939 --> 00:04:01.541
$1.600.000.

13
00:04:01.641 --> 00:04:05.168
Bids to all now.
at 1.600.000--

14
00:04:05.211 --> 00:04:07.013
1.650.000.

15
00:04:07.113 --> 00:04:11.345
1.650.000.
1.675.000.

16
00:04:11.384 --> 00:04:13.648
Is that a bid. sir?
Don't be shy.

17
00:04:13.686 --> 00:04:17.417
All right then. I'll take it.
1.700.000.

18
00:04:17.457 --> 00:04:20.756
1.725.000.
1.725.000.

19
00:04:20.793 --> 00:04:22.562
1.750.000.
Thank you.

20
00:04:22.662 --> 00:04:24.430
The bid is $1.750.000.

21
00:04:24.530 --> 00:04:27.363
- 1.775.000 on my left.
- Mr. Morritz.

22
00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:31.564
Please don't let me forget this.

23
00:04:31.604 --> 00:04:34.198
1.775.000 on my left.

24
00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:35.675
Against the telephone now.

25
00:04:35.775 --> 00:04:39.108
Against you. sir.
1.775.000.

26
00:04:39.145 --> 00:04:42.205
1.810.000?
1.810.000.

27
00:04:42.248 --> 00:04:46.708
1.850.000.
1.875.000 on my left.

28
00:04:46.753 --> 00:04:48.221
In the room--

29
00:04:48.321 --> 00:04:50.482
1.900.000?

30
00:04:50.523 --> 00:04:52.225
1.920.000 in the room.

31
00:04:52.325 --> 00:04:55.453
Yes. I got you. sir.
1.940.000.

32
00:04:55.495 --> 00:04:58.658
Not yours. ma'am.
Neither of yours.

33
00:04:58.698 --> 00:05:02.327
$1.940.000.

34
00:05:02.935 --> 00:05:03.670
I'll take 10.

35
00:05:03.770 --> 00:05:06.864
Do you want back in. sir?
Is that a yes? No?

36
00:05:06.906 --> 00:05:11.673
The Stradivarius now at $1.940.000.

37
00:05:11.711 --> 00:05:13.711
1.950.000 on my left.

38
00:05:13.713 --> 00:05:14.781
Down to you two.

39
00:05:14.881 --> 00:05:17.816
1.950.000.
Not yours. sir?

40
00:05:17.850 --> 00:05:22.287
Not yours?
1.950.000.

41
00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:24.090
All done then?

42
00:05:24.190 --> 00:05:25.558
Fair warning.

43
00:05:25.658 --> 00:05:29.094
I'm selling now at $1.950.000.

44
00:05:29.128 --> 00:05:33.292
And sold to the lady on my left.

45
00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:35.927

46
00:05:40.907 --> 00:05:44.536
The last sale of the evening.
lot number 72.

47
00:05:44.577 --> 00:05:46.577
on the turntable there.

48
00:05:46.612 --> 00:05:48.481
The star of the night--

49
00:05:48.581 --> 00:05:50.083
and-- where is she?

50
00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:55.485
The last violin of Niccolò Bussotti. 1 681.

51
00:05:55.521 --> 00:05:57.989
A masterpiece of the Golden Age.

52
00:05:58.024 --> 00:06:02.358
And. if she will give us the pleasure.

53
00:06:03.363 --> 00:06:05.957
And here she is now.
lot 72.

54
00:06:05.998 --> 00:06:10.196
the so-called Red Violin.

55
00:06:10.236 --> 00:06:12.704
At this time the last order bid

56
00:06:12.739 --> 00:06:14.207
is at $250.000.

57
00:06:14.307 --> 00:06:17.037
A lot of interest here.
of course.

58
00:06:17.076 --> 00:06:19.646
So. now let's open the floor
and who will start us off?

59
00:06:19.746 --> 00:06:22.715
260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

60
00:06:22.749 --> 00:06:26.082
270.000--

61
00:06:26.119 --> 00:06:28.679

62
00:06:49.575 --> 00:06:51.575
Madame?

63
00:06:55.014 --> 00:06:57.812
Cesca. can you still see the future?

64
00:06:57.850 --> 00:07:00.080
Are you all right?

65
00:07:00.119 --> 00:07:01.354
Sit down.

66
00:07:01.454 --> 00:07:04.389
Did you call me?
I was in the garden.

67
00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:07.325
- I can come here. can't I?
- Of course.

68
00:07:07.360 --> 00:07:11.797
- This is part of my house.
- Of course. madame.

69
00:07:13.933 --> 00:07:14.901
I have...

70
00:07:15.001 --> 00:07:19.870
some new amulets and bones for you.

71
00:07:20.173 --> 00:07:25.509
If your husband spits on them.
it will help.

72
00:07:26.245 --> 00:07:27.814
Are you hungry?

73
00:07:27.914 --> 00:07:30.906
Don't eat that. it's fish.

74
00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:31.517
So?

75
00:07:31.617 --> 00:07:36.350
Your child will be slow to learn.

76
00:07:38.858 --> 00:07:41.986
I also have some stones for you...

77
00:07:42.028 --> 00:07:45.486
and a key to wear around your neck.

78
00:07:45.531 --> 00:07:47.701
My husband's tired of spitting.

79
00:07:47.733 --> 00:07:50.224
Spitting's what men are good for.

80
00:07:50.269 --> 00:07:54.535
A father's saliva-- the best thing he can give.

81
00:07:55.575 --> 00:07:56.676
Cesca...

82
00:07:56.776 --> 00:08:00.007
tell me my child's future.

83
00:08:00.246 --> 00:08:01.881
I can't do that.

84
00:08:01.981 --> 00:08:04.245
Don't worry about my husband.

85
00:08:04.283 --> 00:08:07.775
It's not your husband.

86
00:08:07.820 --> 00:08:11.256
I'm simply not able to do it.

87
00:08:12.859 --> 00:08:13.960
I see.

88
00:08:14.060 --> 00:08:16.995
Until the baby is born...

89
00:08:17.029 --> 00:08:20.362
your humors are one.

90
00:08:21.400 --> 00:08:23.493
However...

91
00:08:24.203 --> 00:08:26.262
I can read your future.

92
00:08:26.305 --> 00:08:29.069
No. I told you. I'm scared.

93
00:08:29.108 --> 00:08:31.508
Come on. madame.

94
00:08:32.211 --> 00:08:34.236
Five cards.

95
00:08:36.716 --> 00:08:39.480
It's only the future.

96
00:08:39.619 --> 00:08:41.985
What if it's bad?

97
00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:45.415
I'll pretend not to see it.

98
00:09:07.947 --> 00:09:09.947
Tell me everything.

99
00:09:19.091 --> 00:09:21.091
The moon.

100
00:09:22.061 --> 00:09:23.196
You'll live...

101
00:09:23.296 --> 00:09:28.598
a long life. full and rich.

102
00:09:29.702 --> 00:09:31.761
There's--

103
00:09:31.804 --> 00:09:34.830
there's travel ahead.

104
00:09:35.808 --> 00:09:37.543
I see...

105
00:09:37.643 --> 00:09:40.237
a long journey.

106
00:09:46.452 --> 00:09:48.452
Niccolò?

107
00:09:50.890 --> 00:09:52.890
Leave us.

108
00:09:57.029 --> 00:09:59.122
Close the door.

109
00:10:01.968 --> 00:10:02.435
What is it?

110
00:10:02.535 --> 00:10:06.437
Why do you come here in your condition?

111
00:10:06.472 --> 00:10:09.373
- I know I'll find you here.
- What is it?

112
00:10:09.408 --> 00:10:12.070
- I talked to Cesca.
- And?

113
00:10:12.111 --> 00:10:13.713
She read my future.

114
00:10:13.813 --> 00:10:14.981
Cesca! Dear God!

115
00:10:15.081 --> 00:10:20.280
And the birth. she said. will be
very difficult. and painful.

116
00:10:20.319 --> 00:10:21.854
They always are.

117
00:10:21.954 --> 00:10:24.891
- This is no prediction!
- We're talking about me!

118
00:10:24.991 --> 00:10:29.052
Why do you listen to Cesca?
She is our servant.

119
00:10:29.095 --> 00:10:33.031
I have an excellent midwife.
an astrologer. a doctor.

120
00:10:33.065 --> 00:10:35.966
They'll all be there.
It will be perfect.

121
00:10:36.002 --> 00:10:39.438
- I know.
- How do you know?

122
00:10:39.472 --> 00:10:41.472
I know.

123
00:10:50.583 --> 00:10:54.212
I'm too old to be having a baby.

124
00:11:17.643 --> 00:11:19.941
This is a violin.

125
00:11:23.716 --> 00:11:28.119
- It's different.
- I still have to varnish it.

126
00:11:28.821 --> 00:11:31.255
But there's something--

127
00:11:31.290 --> 00:11:32.758
It's perfect.

128
00:11:32.858 --> 00:11:34.327
Everything else here is junk...

129
00:11:34.427 --> 00:11:38.864
worthy of a peddler.
or the trash heap.

130
00:11:38.898 --> 00:11:41.662
But this is my masterpiece.

131
00:11:43.836 --> 00:11:46.532
I made it for our son. Anna.

132
00:11:46.572 --> 00:11:49.541
Our son will be a musician.

133
00:11:49.575 --> 00:11:51.839
He'll live for music.

134
00:11:51.877 --> 00:11:56.644
He'll bring us pride.
and beauty to the world.

135
00:11:57.483 --> 00:12:01.886
I wanted to surprise you.
but you see...

136
00:12:01.921 --> 00:12:04.788
I can also make predictions.

137
00:12:04.824 --> 00:12:07.918
It's too big for a baby.

138
00:12:09.562 --> 00:12:11.689
He'll grow.

139
00:12:21.574 --> 00:12:25.408
My child will come when the moon is full.

140
00:12:25.644 --> 00:12:26.946
Come to bed.

141
00:12:27.046 --> 00:12:30.015
You're jealous of our relationship.

142
00:12:30.049 --> 00:12:31.751
Me and the moon.

143
00:12:31.851 --> 00:12:34.445
No. I'm not jealous.

144
00:12:34.487 --> 00:12:37.047
I know you'll come back.

145
00:12:47.566 --> 00:12:50.000

146
00:14:20.226 --> 00:14:23.195
Master. a boy is asking for you.

147
00:14:23.229 --> 00:14:24.630
Tell him to go away.

148
00:14:24.730 --> 00:14:28.166
He won't. sir.
The doctor sent him.

149
00:14:28.200 --> 00:14:30.200
I think you'd better come.

150
00:14:30.202 --> 00:14:32.232
Your wife. sir-- the doctor--

151
00:14:32.271 --> 00:14:35.297
- What is it?
- She's not well.

152
00:14:35.341 --> 00:14:37.775
Having the baby.

153
00:15:38.270 --> 00:15:40.270
Get out.

154
00:15:40.439 --> 00:15:44.933
Get out! Leave me alone.
for God's sake!

155
00:18:28.974 --> 00:18:31.238
1.650.000.

156
00:18:31.276 --> 00:18:33.767
1.675.000.

157
00:18:33.812 --> 00:18:36.248
Is that a bid. sir?
Don't be shy. I'll take it.

158
00:18:36.348 --> 00:18:38.183
- 1.700.000--
- Excuse me. Mr. Ruselsky.

159
00:18:38.283 --> 00:18:39.585
1.725.000.

160
00:18:39.685 --> 00:18:42.449
The Stradivarius now at 1.725.000.

161
00:18:42.488 --> 00:18:44.513
Paul at 1.750.000.

162
00:18:44.556 --> 00:18:46.820
1.775.000 on the left.

163
00:18:46.859 --> 00:18:49.194
Against the telephone now.
Against you. sir.

164
00:18:49.294 --> 00:18:51.762
1.775.000.
1.810.000.

165
00:18:51.797 --> 00:18:54.357
1.810.000.
1.850.000.

166
00:18:54.399 --> 00:18:57.596
1.850.000.
1.875.000.

167
00:18:57.636 --> 00:19:01.572
- 1.900.000--
- Son of a bitch.

168
00:19:01.607 --> 00:19:05.008
- He knows nothing.
- Who? Who?

169
00:19:05.043 --> 00:19:05.978
Morritz.

170
00:19:06.078 --> 00:19:08.546
$1.940.000.

171
00:19:08.580 --> 00:19:11.640
1.950.000 on the left.

172
00:19:11.683 --> 00:19:12.651
All done then?

173
00:19:12.751 --> 00:19:16.847
I'm selling now at $1.950.000.

174
00:19:16.889 --> 00:19:20.689
And sold to the lady on my left.

175
00:19:26.965 --> 00:19:29.168
Now. ladies and gentlemen.
the last sale of the evening.

176
00:19:29.268 --> 00:19:32.704
Iot number 72.
the star of the night--

177
00:19:32.738 --> 00:19:33.872
where is she?

178
00:19:33.972 --> 00:19:38.272
The last violin of Niccolò Bussotti. 1 681.

179
00:19:38.310 --> 00:19:40.676
A masterpiece of the Golden Age.

180
00:19:40.712 --> 00:19:42.714
If she will give us the pleasure.

181
00:19:42.814 --> 00:19:47.410
And there she is now.
lot number 72.

182
00:19:47.452 --> 00:19:49.818
the so-called Red Violin.

183
00:19:49.855 --> 00:19:52.756
The last order bid is at $250.000.

184
00:19:52.791 --> 00:19:55.089
Who will start us off?
260.000.

185
00:19:55.127 --> 00:19:57.254
Good evening.
Mr. Ruselsky.

186
00:20:46.945 --> 00:20:50.403
You must clean the violin every day.

187
00:20:51.016 --> 00:20:52.551
Care for it well.

188
00:20:52.651 --> 00:20:57.884
This is your violin for as long
as you're at the orphanage.

189
00:22:12.397 --> 00:22:15.195
A curse hangs over you. madame.

190
00:22:15.233 --> 00:22:19.863
Danger to those who come under your thrall.

191
00:22:19.905 --> 00:22:22.567
And there will be many...

192
00:22:22.607 --> 00:22:24.409
many.

193
00:22:24.509 --> 00:22:29.003
It is a powerful card.
the Hanged Man.

194
00:22:29.548 --> 00:22:32.813
I see-- I see danger...

195
00:22:32.851 --> 00:22:36.116
infirmity and disease.

196
00:22:37.489 --> 00:22:41.323
I'm sorry. but what kind I can't say.

197
00:22:41.560 --> 00:22:45.360
There are many kinds of sickness.

198
00:23:07.686 --> 00:23:10.484
These roads.
Brother Christophe!

199
00:23:10.522 --> 00:23:15.221
You've no idea what I've endured.
And why such haste?

200
00:23:15.260 --> 00:23:20.527
What is so urgent it couldn't
wait until my next visit?

201
00:23:20.565 --> 00:23:22.134
We have a boy. sir.

202
00:23:22.234 --> 00:23:23.935
You have many boys!

203
00:23:24.035 --> 00:23:26.970
This boy is a miracle.
You'll see.

204
00:23:27.005 --> 00:23:29.974
Vienna swarms with miracles.

205
00:23:30.008 --> 00:23:31.009
Not like him.

206
00:23:31.109 --> 00:23:34.567
We felt you should see him at once.

207
00:23:35.080 --> 00:23:36.515
Does he speak French?

208
00:23:36.615 --> 00:23:38.383
No. sir. Unfortunately.

209
00:23:38.483 --> 00:23:42.249
All your students should learn French.

210
00:23:42.287 --> 00:23:44.551
It's the language of music.

211
00:23:44.589 --> 00:23:48.753
It hones the ear and elevates the mind!

212
00:24:03.642 --> 00:24:05.377
Monsieur Poussin...

213
00:24:05.477 --> 00:24:08.275
this is Kaspar Weiss.

214
00:24:11.283 --> 00:24:14.218
What violin is this?

215
00:24:14.286 --> 00:24:16.982
I haven't seen it before.

216
00:24:17.022 --> 00:24:19.684
We've had it for 100 years.

217
00:24:19.724 --> 00:24:21.593
Far too big for him.

218
00:24:21.693 --> 00:24:23.495
Look at his hands.

219
00:24:23.595 --> 00:24:26.655
He should play on a child's violin.

220
00:24:26.698 --> 00:24:28.333
Even Mozart...

221
00:24:28.433 --> 00:24:31.036
God rest his soul.
played in Versailles...

222
00:24:31.136 --> 00:24:33.195
on a child's violin.

223
00:24:33.238 --> 00:24:35.570
No shame in that.

224
00:24:35.607 --> 00:24:38.940
Wouldn't you like a smaller instrument?

225
00:24:38.977 --> 00:24:41.309
He seems to manage.

226
00:24:42.681 --> 00:24:45.673
Let him try.

227
00:24:46.551 --> 00:24:48.551
Play. my boy.

228
00:24:48.854 --> 00:24:50.854
Play.

229
00:26:23.548 --> 00:26:25.548
I see.

230
00:26:30.388 --> 00:26:32.413
Monsieur Poussin?

231
00:26:32.457 --> 00:26:37.394
We're prepared to offer a small sum

232
00:26:37.429 --> 00:26:40.489
to help him in his study.

233
00:26:59.317 --> 00:27:04.755
They say you're a good boy.
well-mannered and clean.

234
00:27:04.789 --> 00:27:06.358
Glad to hear it.

235
00:27:06.458 --> 00:27:08.790
But you don't like vegetables.

236
00:27:08.827 --> 00:27:10.262
Is that so?

237
00:27:10.362 --> 00:27:11.796
Yes. sir.

238
00:27:11.896 --> 00:27:13.365
What don't you like?

239
00:27:13.465 --> 00:27:15.865
Carrots. sir...

240
00:27:15.900 --> 00:27:18.494
and beans and cabbage--

241
00:27:18.536 --> 00:27:20.536
These monks can't cook.

242
00:27:23.575 --> 00:27:26.442
They also write you've a weak heart.

243
00:27:26.478 --> 00:27:28.478
Is that so?

244
00:27:29.681 --> 00:27:33.378
You must have a strong heart
to play the violin.

245
00:27:33.418 --> 00:27:34.986
Believe me.

246
00:27:35.086 --> 00:27:37.919
And stronger still to live in Vienna.

247
00:27:37.956 --> 00:27:41.892
You shall see.
Vienna is an infuriating city...

248
00:27:41.926 --> 00:27:45.453
infuriating. but magnificent.

249
00:28:42.554 --> 00:28:44.554
Magnificent...

250
00:28:44.556 --> 00:28:46.922
this city!

251
00:28:50.495 --> 00:28:52.495
Antoinette!

252
00:28:53.398 --> 00:28:55.398
May I present to you...

253
00:28:57.402 --> 00:28:59.270
Kaspar Weiss.

254
00:28:59.370 --> 00:29:02.305
One of the most gifted children on earth.

255
00:29:02.340 --> 00:29:04.570
But. Georges. we can't--

256
00:29:05.810 --> 00:29:08.904
My wife. Antoinette Poussin.

257
00:29:08.947 --> 00:29:10.715
Good afternoon. Kaspar.

258
00:29:10.815 --> 00:29:13.682
How nice to meet you.

259
00:29:13.718 --> 00:29:17.950
Go on in. I'll show you your room in a minute.

260
00:29:17.989 --> 00:29:21.356
Georges. please.
We can't afford to keep him!

261
00:29:21.392 --> 00:29:23.392
We can't afford not to.

262
00:29:26.331 --> 00:29:30.768
There's something about
your playing that eludes me.

263
00:29:30.802 --> 00:29:34.795
I've decided to analyze it systematically...

264
00:29:34.839 --> 00:29:36.708
with a scientific method.

265
00:29:36.808 --> 00:29:38.543
First...

266
00:29:38.643 --> 00:29:40.111
your bowing...

267
00:29:40.211 --> 00:29:42.372
and your left hand phrasing.

268
00:29:42.413 --> 00:29:46.179
Your détaché. ornamentation and your taste.

269
00:29:46.217 --> 00:29:47.519
And theory!

270
00:29:47.619 --> 00:29:49.712
Theory. too. is important.

271
00:29:51.022 --> 00:29:55.618
You need a lot more than
inspiration to play the violin.

272
00:29:55.660 --> 00:29:58.754
You need method.
You must think...

273
00:29:59.864 --> 00:30:01.399
and work.

274
00:30:01.499 --> 00:30:03.763
Won't you eat?

275
00:30:03.802 --> 00:30:05.003
You must eat!

276
00:30:05.103 --> 00:30:06.671
Did you want something else?

277
00:30:06.771 --> 00:30:09.706
Try this cheese.
I think you'll like it.

278
00:30:09.741 --> 00:30:11.741
It's French!

279
00:30:12.977 --> 00:30:15.605
- Try some.
- Taste it.

280
00:30:18.349 --> 00:30:23.480
You'll see. a little different
from the monks' crumbly cheese!

281
00:30:23.521 --> 00:30:25.521
Go on!

282
00:30:25.523 --> 00:30:26.458
Kaspar...

283
00:30:26.558 --> 00:30:30.426
if you play well.
you'll enjoy the finest fare.

284
00:30:30.461 --> 00:30:33.123
We can't afford coal.
let alone food!

285
00:30:33.164 --> 00:30:35.066
Sell your jewelry!
Sell your David!

286
00:30:35.166 --> 00:30:38.269
Besides he voted
to behead the king. the monster!

287
00:30:38.369 --> 00:30:40.462
My boy...

288
00:30:40.505 --> 00:30:44.032
play well.
and there will be cheese.

289
00:30:44.075 --> 00:30:46.873
Violin... cheese.

290
00:30:48.146 --> 00:30:50.146
May I go to my room now?

291
00:30:50.148 --> 00:30:52.241
Go ahead.
And sleep well.

292
00:30:53.318 --> 00:30:56.082
Madame will assist you in your prayers.

293
00:31:00.058 --> 00:31:01.593
Why speak French?

294
00:31:01.693 --> 00:31:05.151
- He doesn't understand.
- So he'll learn!

295
00:31:06.364 --> 00:31:09.265
I want them to know who taught him!

296
00:31:24.449 --> 00:31:26.449
Good morning. Poussin.

297
00:31:27.852 --> 00:31:30.922
I pride myself on visiting the Taufer Orphanage

298
00:31:31.022 --> 00:31:34.924
three times a year to offer
my services as a teacher.

299
00:31:34.959 --> 00:31:39.293
as a gesture of support
for those good men of the cloth.

300
00:31:39.330 --> 00:31:42.458
This year. they called early.

301
00:31:42.500 --> 00:31:45.469
I was skeptical. but...

302
00:31:45.503 --> 00:31:48.336
when this child raised his bow...

303
00:31:48.373 --> 00:31:53.174
when he played his first note.
well. Baron von Spielmann...

304
00:31:53.211 --> 00:31:55.873
I knew my prayers had been answered.

305
00:31:55.914 --> 00:31:58.906
You've unearthed another Wunderkind.

306
00:32:02.987 --> 00:32:05.182
I've no money for you. Poussin.

307
00:32:05.223 --> 00:32:07.953
I have no concerts to offer you.

308
00:32:09.093 --> 00:32:11.323
It isn't the money.

309
00:32:11.362 --> 00:32:14.195
I suggest you find another patron.

310
00:32:14.232 --> 00:32:16.232
Must I beg?

311
00:32:17.402 --> 00:32:19.632
Isn't that what you're doing?

312
00:32:19.671 --> 00:32:21.671
Yes...

313
00:32:21.906 --> 00:32:23.906
I am.

314
00:32:24.676 --> 00:32:26.871
In three weeks...

315
00:32:26.911 --> 00:32:31.177
I'm holding a private audition at my salon.

316
00:32:32.216 --> 00:32:34.582
Prince Mannsfeld is leaving...

317
00:32:34.619 --> 00:32:35.787
for Prussia...

318
00:32:35.887 --> 00:32:38.879
and seeks a prodigy to accompany him.

319
00:32:38.923 --> 00:32:40.923
He must hear this boy.

320
00:32:41.492 --> 00:32:44.791
Three weeks.
Can you be ready? Truthfully?

321
00:32:44.829 --> 00:32:46.698
I could be ready tomorrow.

322
00:32:46.798 --> 00:32:49.198
Be very certain. Poussin.

323
00:32:49.233 --> 00:32:51.428
If you embarrass me again--

324
00:32:51.469 --> 00:32:56.065
I've charmed the crowned heads of France.

325
00:32:56.107 --> 00:32:58.667
Where are those heads now?

326
00:32:58.710 --> 00:33:01.720
Rolling in the gutters of the new Republic!

327
00:33:18.863 --> 00:33:21.229
No. no. no. no!

328
00:33:21.265 --> 00:33:24.063
The first phrase.
the entire section.

329
00:33:24.102 --> 00:33:25.803
must be played staccato.

330
00:33:25.903 --> 00:33:30.602
A modern style. well and good.
but let's not be crude.

331
00:33:30.641 --> 00:33:31.809
You liked it. didn't you?

332
00:33:31.909 --> 00:33:34.207
- Yes.
- I'm delighted.

333
00:33:34.245 --> 00:33:37.908
You're going to play it
again and again and again.

334
00:33:38.950 --> 00:33:41.714

335
00:33:47.925 --> 00:33:52.021
See this? It's a clockwork
chronometer. of my invention.

336
00:33:52.063 --> 00:33:54.964
It's called the Poussin-meter.

337
00:33:56.134 --> 00:34:00.002
You will heed it with
the same deference you would me.

338
00:34:01.372 --> 00:34:05.604
What you just played corresponds to a tempo...

339
00:34:05.643 --> 00:34:07.643
like this.

340
00:34:11.449 --> 00:34:13.917
Each day. as we progress

341
00:34:13.951 --> 00:34:17.717
we shall push down this little ball one notch.

342
00:34:17.755 --> 00:34:22.317
Until finally. in three weeks.
you'll be playing like this.

343
00:34:26.664 --> 00:34:28.664
The world will be yours.

344
00:34:29.801 --> 00:34:33.581
Antoinette. there's something
I still don't understand.

345
00:34:35.339 --> 00:34:38.035
His violin has a wonderful sound.

346
00:34:38.076 --> 00:34:39.410
and a lovely form.

347
00:34:39.510 --> 00:34:41.637
Of course. it's Italian.

348
00:34:41.679 --> 00:34:44.045
Is it very valuable?

349
00:34:45.583 --> 00:34:47.642
Why do you ask?

350
00:34:47.685 --> 00:34:51.121
Well. we could pay the rent.
if ever--

351
00:34:51.155 --> 00:34:54.386
He will play divinely. my dear.

352
00:34:54.425 --> 00:34:56.094
Can't you trust me?

353
00:34:56.194 --> 00:34:58.628
Yes. of course I can.

354
00:34:58.663 --> 00:35:02.497
But must he sleep with it?
He could roll over on it.

355
00:35:02.533 --> 00:35:04.202
What?

356
00:35:04.302 --> 00:35:06.302
He sleeps with it?

357
00:35:06.804 --> 00:35:08.906
Straight. proud.
Lift your chin. There.

358
00:35:09.006 --> 00:35:12.100
Perfect. your bow.
You're clutching.

359
00:35:12.143 --> 00:35:14.941
Your body's stiff.
your elbow's locked.

360
00:35:16.280 --> 00:35:18.583
I knew something was holding you back.

361
00:35:18.683 --> 00:35:22.673
Something. but I didn't know what.
Now it's totally clear.

362
00:35:23.688 --> 00:35:28.125
You're oppressed by your violin.
It has you completely enslaved.

363
00:35:28.159 --> 00:35:31.390
Look at you.
There. very good.

364
00:35:33.698 --> 00:35:37.794
If you want to advance.
Kaspar Weiss. you must let go.

365
00:35:38.970 --> 00:35:42.167
What do you mean. sir?
I don't understand.

366
00:35:44.142 --> 00:35:47.475
Antoinette tells me you sleep with your violin.

367
00:35:48.579 --> 00:35:51.707
Tonight you'll sleep by yourself.

368
00:35:51.749 --> 00:35:53.774
Without the violin.

369
00:35:53.818 --> 00:35:55.818
Without your violin.

370
00:36:08.199 --> 00:36:10.599
Thank you for coming so quickly.

371
00:36:14.872 --> 00:36:17.636
Thank you so much. Doctor.
Good night.

372
00:36:22.880 --> 00:36:24.315
Feeling better?

373
00:36:24.415 --> 00:36:25.950
Yes. thank you.

374
00:36:26.050 --> 00:36:30.817
The doctor says that your heart
must have stopped for a minute.

375
00:36:30.855 --> 00:36:32.190
I'm sorry.

376
00:36:32.290 --> 00:36:36.192
It's all right. but we don't
want it to happen again.

377
00:36:37.762 --> 00:36:40.094
Were you worried?

378
00:36:40.131 --> 00:36:43.897
Were you nervous about the audition?

379
00:36:43.935 --> 00:36:46.096
It will be just fine.

380
00:36:46.137 --> 00:36:48.799
- You know that. don't you?
- Georges!

381
00:36:49.640 --> 00:36:51.209
I know. I know.

382
00:36:51.309 --> 00:36:55.439
Kaspar. we want to tell you.

383
00:36:55.479 --> 00:36:58.915
you don't have to do it if you don't want to.

384
00:36:58.950 --> 00:37:01.111
You don't have to play.

385
00:37:01.152 --> 00:37:02.854
I don't?

386
00:37:02.954 --> 00:37:05.889
We can cancel the audition.

387
00:37:05.923 --> 00:37:08.118
We'll manage. somehow.

388
00:37:09.660 --> 00:37:12.663
It's better than making you sick. do you see?

389
00:37:12.763 --> 00:37:15.231
You don't have to be famous.

390
00:37:15.266 --> 00:37:16.734
No?

391
00:37:16.834 --> 00:37:18.834
Yes.

392
00:37:19.103 --> 00:37:20.571
Oui.

393
00:37:20.671 --> 00:37:22.671
I'm sick.

394
00:37:23.774 --> 00:37:27.073
I want to be famous.

395
00:37:27.111 --> 00:37:29.602
Sir. I really do.

396
00:37:29.647 --> 00:37:32.138
That's my boy.

397
00:37:32.183 --> 00:37:34.378
I'm very proud of you.

398
00:37:34.418 --> 00:37:36.579
I want you to rest. relax.

399
00:37:36.621 --> 00:37:38.748
Madame Poussin will bring

400
00:37:38.789 --> 00:37:41.053
a visitor you like very much.

401
00:37:46.397 --> 00:37:48.397
Thank you. madame.

402
00:38:00.645 --> 00:38:02.645
Good!

403
00:39:02.606 --> 00:39:04.606
There you go!

404
00:39:38.576 --> 00:39:40.601
We better sleep now.

405
00:39:40.644 --> 00:39:43.477
Tomorrow's going to be a busy day.

406
00:40:17.782 --> 00:40:18.883
Perfect.

407
00:40:18.983 --> 00:40:21.884
And now. backwards.
Are you ready?

408
00:41:01.492 --> 00:41:04.120
Rejected! The shame!

409
00:41:11.302 --> 00:41:13.302
Kaspar Weiss.

410
00:41:13.971 --> 00:41:16.599
Kaspar Weiss. violin!

411
00:41:16.640 --> 00:41:18.640
Play the best you can.

412
00:41:18.676 --> 00:41:20.676
Play your best.

413
00:41:46.637 --> 00:41:48.867

414
00:41:50.608 --> 00:41:55.170
Master Poussin and his protégé. Kaspar Weiss.

415
00:42:07.424 --> 00:42:09.093
Closer.

416
00:42:09.193 --> 00:42:11.193
Come closer.

417
00:42:14.231 --> 00:42:18.565
So you're the wild child I've heard all about.

418
00:42:18.602 --> 00:42:21.901
An orphan raised by monks.

419
00:42:21.939 --> 00:42:24.599
If you prefer.
we can call in the next.

420
00:42:25.576 --> 00:42:26.710
There's the son of--

421
00:42:26.810 --> 00:42:28.810
No. no.

422
00:42:29.146 --> 00:42:30.648
How charming to think

423
00:42:30.748 --> 00:42:34.445
a monastery has actually produced something--

424
00:42:34.485 --> 00:42:36.485
something worthwhile.

425
00:42:38.889 --> 00:42:41.409
That's a lovely instrument you have.

426
00:42:42.159 --> 00:42:44.159
May I see it?

427
00:42:44.328 --> 00:42:46.387
May I see it. my boy?

428
00:42:58.342 --> 00:43:00.342
Is it for sale?

429
00:43:01.145 --> 00:43:04.308
I'd give you a good price for it.

430
00:43:05.583 --> 00:43:08.052
He's very attached to his instrument.

431
00:43:08.152 --> 00:43:10.152
So I see.

432
00:43:10.621 --> 00:43:13.886
Perhaps after he's played--

433
00:43:13.924 --> 00:43:17.792
Of course. let him play.
I might take him. too.

434
00:43:17.828 --> 00:43:20.160
Come. play for me.

435
00:43:22.633 --> 00:43:25.932
Won't you play something for me?
Please.

436
00:43:26.637 --> 00:43:28.637
Poussin!

437
00:43:33.410 --> 00:43:36.038
Just play for him. son.

438
00:43:36.080 --> 00:43:38.080
Play.

439
00:43:46.957 --> 00:43:49.221

440
00:43:59.803 --> 00:44:02.323

441
00:44:44.214 --> 00:44:46.705

442
00:45:25.789 --> 00:45:27.789
Monsieur Poussin?

443
00:45:29.593 --> 00:45:32.721
On behalf of the brothers I thank you

444
00:45:32.763 --> 00:45:35.857
for the generosity you showed Kaspar.

445
00:45:35.899 --> 00:45:39.596
He takes with him the many gifts you gave him.

446
00:45:39.636 --> 00:45:41.763
I did what I could.

447
00:45:41.805 --> 00:45:45.571
Would you honor us
by sharing our modest supper?

448
00:45:45.609 --> 00:45:48.373
It's very kind of you.

449
00:45:48.412 --> 00:45:52.212
but my wife awaits me.
all of Vienna awaits me.

450
00:45:53.317 --> 00:45:56.514
Of course. we understand.

451
00:45:57.621 --> 00:45:59.390
I do have one question.

452
00:45:59.490 --> 00:46:01.325
Yes?

453
00:46:01.425 --> 00:46:03.260
The violin.

454
00:46:03.360 --> 00:46:05.360
Yes?

455
00:46:06.263 --> 00:46:08.561
What will become of it?

456
00:46:09.466 --> 00:46:13.334
I'm sorry.
I thought you knew.

457
00:46:13.370 --> 00:46:16.737
Naturally you were foremost in our thoughts.

458
00:46:16.774 --> 00:46:20.232
After all the time and energy you invested

459
00:46:20.277 --> 00:46:22.438
it would be wrong

460
00:46:22.479 --> 00:46:25.414
to give it to another child.

461
00:46:25.449 --> 00:46:27.051
Yes. of course.

462
00:46:27.151 --> 00:46:29.984
So we buried it with the boy.

463
00:46:30.020 --> 00:46:32.488
He can play it in heaven.

464
00:46:37.861 --> 00:46:39.861
Yes. quite right.

465
00:46:54.745 --> 00:46:59.341
And then I see a time of life.

466
00:47:00.017 --> 00:47:02.815
a time of lust and energy.

467
00:47:02.853 --> 00:47:08.052
Ioosed across mountains and oceans and time.

468
00:47:10.894 --> 00:47:13.454
Confusing. madame. I know.

469
00:47:13.497 --> 00:47:15.658
But I see it.

470
00:47:15.699 --> 00:47:17.699
I'm certain.

471
00:47:18.535 --> 00:47:20.765
Yours is a Lazarus soul.

472
00:49:31.835 --> 00:49:33.996
Yes. I see.

473
00:49:34.037 --> 00:49:36.767
Put her through.
will you?

474
00:49:38.342 --> 00:49:40.674
We're on hold.

475
00:49:40.711 --> 00:49:44.477
You should tell her our story.
Explain its past.

476
00:49:44.514 --> 00:49:48.151
Brother. please. she doesn't care.
She's doing her job.

477
00:49:48.251 --> 00:49:50.515
But if you convince her--

478
00:49:50.554 --> 00:49:51.722
Father Victor.

479
00:49:51.822 --> 00:49:53.790
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

480
00:49:53.890 --> 00:49:55.025
This is Suzanne.

481
00:49:55.125 --> 00:49:57.127
They're just closing on lot 71.

482
00:49:57.227 --> 00:50:00.663
Can you hear the auctioneer?

483
00:50:00.697 --> 00:50:02.756
Sold to the lady on the left.

484
00:50:03.800 --> 00:50:05.800
Yes. I can hear him.

485
00:50:05.802 --> 00:50:09.499
Suzanne. how do I tell you when I want to bid?

486
00:50:09.539 --> 00:50:13.498
Leave it to me. sir. Just tell
me when you want to stop.

487
00:50:13.543 --> 00:50:16.113
A masterpiece of the Golden Age.

488
00:50:16.213 --> 00:50:18.315
And. if she will give us the pleasure.

489
00:50:18.415 --> 00:50:21.775
I feel helpless.
Isn't there something we can do?

490
00:50:22.552 --> 00:50:23.954
Yes.

491
00:50:24.054 --> 00:50:25.856
We can pray.

492
00:50:25.956 --> 00:50:27.057
Auctioneer:...interest here. of course.

493
00:50:27.157 --> 00:50:29.318
Last order bid at $250.000.

494
00:50:29.359 --> 00:50:32.729
So. now let's open the floor
and who will start us off?

495
00:50:32.829 --> 00:50:35.923
260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

496
00:50:35.966 --> 00:50:38.696
270.000.
Suzanne on the telephone.

497
00:50:38.735 --> 00:50:41.568
280.000.
Back to you. sir.

498
00:50:41.605 --> 00:50:45.245
300.000. I see you. Suzanne.
Against your caller now.

499
00:50:48.512 --> 00:50:50.512
And then...

500
00:50:52.182 --> 00:50:55.310
a man comes into your life--

501
00:50:55.352 --> 00:50:57.445
a handsome man--

502
00:50:57.487 --> 00:50:59.785
and intelligent.

503
00:50:59.823 --> 00:51:02.553
He'll seduce you with his talent

504
00:51:03.460 --> 00:51:05.587
and worse.

505
00:51:05.629 --> 00:51:07.629
In short...

506
00:51:07.798 --> 00:51:09.798
he's the Devil.

507
00:51:38.128 --> 00:51:40.824
What a marvelous violin.

508
00:51:44.234 --> 00:51:45.736
What do you want?

509
00:51:45.836 --> 00:51:48.939
I was lured by the music.
It drew me across the heath.

510
00:51:49.039 --> 00:51:50.307
Oh. yes?

511
00:51:50.407 --> 00:51:52.309
Maybe you can go back the same way.

512
00:51:52.409 --> 00:51:55.606
I'm your host.
This is my land.

513
00:51:56.913 --> 00:51:59.609
Now I see. my mistake.

514
00:52:01.118 --> 00:52:02.753
We will not be a trouble.

515
00:52:02.853 --> 00:52:05.321
We'll be leaving here by nightfall.

516
00:52:05.355 --> 00:52:07.355
That won't be necessary.

517
00:52:07.390 --> 00:52:10.260
I'm sure we can come to some arrangement.

518
00:52:15.665 --> 00:52:16.767
Excuse me. sir?

519
00:52:16.867 --> 00:52:19.233
I must ask you to leave.

520
00:52:19.269 --> 00:52:21.829
We have an invitation.

521
00:52:21.872 --> 00:52:24.773
You can read?

522
00:52:24.808 --> 00:52:27.276
Personal invitation.

523
00:52:44.661 --> 00:52:46.563
- Evening. Percy.
- Good evening. ma'am.

524
00:52:46.663 --> 00:52:48.565
He's in the dressing room.
warming up.

525
00:52:48.665 --> 00:52:50.665
Not without me. I hope.

526
00:52:57.340 --> 00:53:00.366
Victoria.

527
00:53:04.714 --> 00:53:06.714
I need you.

528
00:53:11.621 --> 00:53:14.419
I feel a composition coming on.

529
00:53:18.461 --> 00:53:20.461
So do I.

530
00:53:23.867 --> 00:53:27.268

531
00:53:34.377 --> 00:53:36.377
Ladies and gentlemen.

532
00:53:36.413 --> 00:53:38.677
if I can have your attention.

533
00:53:38.715 --> 00:53:41.548
Mr. Pope has asked me to announce

534
00:53:41.585 --> 00:53:44.321
that he will be performing this afternoon

535
00:53:44.421 --> 00:53:46.480
on an antique instrument

536
00:53:46.523 --> 00:53:48.923
of the Italian school.

537
00:53:48.959 --> 00:53:53.055
which has revitalized
his affections for the violin.

538
00:53:54.264 --> 00:53:56.789

539
00:54:01.037 --> 00:54:02.372
I...

540
00:54:02.472 --> 00:54:06.238
hope that whets your appetite

541
00:54:06.276 --> 00:54:07.577
somewhat.

542
00:54:07.677 --> 00:54:09.677

543
00:54:20.090 --> 00:54:22.923
Mr. Pope. sir.
whenever you're--

544
00:54:22.959 --> 00:54:25.860
- Oh. darling.
- ready.

545
00:55:18.815 --> 00:55:21.825
I'd like to play for you a new composition.

546
00:55:23.653 --> 00:55:26.850
which came to me recently

547
00:55:26.890 --> 00:55:29.859
in a moment of...

548
00:55:29.893 --> 00:55:32.657
inspiration.

549
00:57:40.023 --> 00:57:41.891
'How did it come to this?

550
00:57:41.991 --> 00:57:45.893
Saints in heaven.
how did it happen to him?

551
00:57:45.929 --> 00:57:47.831
An artist who could not be denied.

552
00:57:47.931 --> 00:57:51.594
A poet in fact.
But a murderer.

553
00:57:51.634 --> 00:57:53.634
No.

554
00:57:55.071 --> 00:57:57.774
Yet the looking-glass image was hard to refute.

555
00:57:57.874 --> 00:58:00.443
His fingers and cuffs
were still ruddy with gore.

556
00:58:00.543 --> 00:58:04.377
And as he watched.
in horror...

557
00:58:06.516 --> 00:58:09.586
the speckles of blood seemed
to multiply before his eyes

558
00:58:09.686 --> 00:58:13.986
like maggots on a fetid corpse.

559
00:58:14.023 --> 00:58:15.959
And what would become of him now?

560
00:58:16.059 --> 00:58:19.517
Where would he run to and where would he hide?

561
00:58:19.562 --> 00:58:21.965
The options just then were depressingly few.

562
00:58:22.065 --> 00:58:25.523
Indeed his mind was already racing east

563
00:58:25.568 --> 00:58:27.871
- across the frozen continent--'
- Darling.

564
00:58:27.971 --> 00:58:30.006
'and over the frozen steppes--'

565
00:58:30.106 --> 00:58:31.241
Darling.

566
00:58:31.341 --> 00:58:34.377
'back to the refuge of his childhood estate.'

567
00:58:34.477 --> 00:58:36.413
I have a theme I want to work out.

568
00:58:36.513 --> 00:58:39.048
''To Russia.' he heard the Cossack call.'

569
00:58:39.148 --> 00:58:41.148
It needs to be addressed.

570
00:58:41.184 --> 00:58:43.494
Can't you see I'm trying to work?

571
00:58:48.024 --> 00:58:49.225
You're so selfish.

572
00:58:49.325 --> 00:58:51.694
It was mutual inspiration I had in mind.

573
00:58:51.794 --> 00:58:54.063
Can't you see I don't need any?
I was writing here like--

574
00:58:54.163 --> 00:58:55.999
My love. don't be angry.

575
00:58:56.099 --> 00:58:59.466
- Oh. please.
- You've only yourself to blame.

576
00:58:59.502 --> 00:59:02.302
It's your beauty that summons the music.

577
00:59:05.642 --> 00:59:08.110
And when it comes...

578
00:59:08.144 --> 00:59:10.442
I must play.

579
00:59:14.684 --> 00:59:16.684
Damn you.

580
00:59:56.459 --> 00:59:58.484
Is this what you wanted?

581
01:00:00.496 --> 01:00:02.496
Is this what you wanted?

582
01:00:48.778 --> 01:00:52.976
'East-- east across the frozen continent

583
01:00:53.016 --> 01:00:55.143
and over the frozen steppes.

584
01:00:55.184 --> 01:00:58.813
back to the refuge of his childhood estate.

585
01:00:58.855 --> 01:01:00.356
'To Russia--

586
01:01:00.456 --> 01:01:04.290
to Russia.' he heard the Cossack call.'

587
01:01:04.327 --> 01:01:07.922
- Frederick.
- My darling.

588
01:01:07.964 --> 01:01:11.024
My one inspiration.

589
01:01:11.067 --> 01:01:13.136
I have something terrible to tell you.

590
01:01:13.236 --> 01:01:15.761
Terrible?

591
01:01:15.805 --> 01:01:17.373
The worst.

592
01:01:17.473 --> 01:01:20.243
It must be most terrible for you to tell me now

593
01:01:20.343 --> 01:01:23.210
and ruin this perfect moment.

594
01:01:24.681 --> 01:01:27.115
Jack has killed the minister.

595
01:01:28.418 --> 01:01:30.418
It was an accident.

596
01:01:30.453 --> 01:01:32.453
I see.

597
01:01:33.690 --> 01:01:36.158
He's now fled to Russia.

598
01:01:36.192 --> 01:01:38.192
Self-imposed exile.

599
01:01:40.063 --> 01:01:42.429
I see.

600
01:01:42.465 --> 01:01:44.465
You're leaving me.

601
01:01:46.202 --> 01:01:48.202
I've never been there

602
01:01:48.237 --> 01:01:50.173
and I don't know what to write

603
01:01:50.273 --> 01:01:53.376
- I have to follow him.
- I can't go. I've concerts.

604
01:01:53.476 --> 01:01:55.476
I know. darling.

605
01:01:58.414 --> 01:02:00.780
Are you very angry?

606
01:02:00.817 --> 01:02:02.817
Why should I be?

607
01:02:33.249 --> 01:02:35.818
'Dearest Frederick.
I've just passed the church

608
01:02:35.918 --> 01:02:37.987
near Charrington.
where Jeffrey was baptized

609
01:02:38.087 --> 01:02:40.456
and I'm quickly approaching
the Rutherford bridge.

610
01:02:40.556 --> 01:02:41.624
In other words.

611
01:02:41.724 --> 01:02:42.959
darling.

612
01:02:43.059 --> 01:02:44.994
we have parted for under 1 0 minutes

613
01:02:45.094 --> 01:02:47.688
and already I'm lost.

614
01:02:47.730 --> 01:02:49.730
I return to my writing

615
01:02:49.766 --> 01:02:52.701
in the hope that these few honest words

616
01:02:52.735 --> 01:02:55.538
- might rejoin our lips...'
- 'Darling Victoria.'

617
01:02:55.638 --> 01:02:58.608
'...bring back your hands
to my shivering skin.'

618
01:02:58.708 --> 01:03:00.576
'You trust in words
in the comfort of letters

619
01:03:00.676 --> 01:03:02.445
in a way that I simply do not.

620
01:03:02.545 --> 01:03:05.682
And no matter the language.
no words can convince me

621
01:03:05.782 --> 01:03:07.884
- that you are not gone--'
- 'Frederick. my love.

622
01:03:07.984 --> 01:03:09.919
it's Moscow at last and my very first night

623
01:03:10.019 --> 01:03:12.044
was unspeakably dreary.

624
01:03:12.088 --> 01:03:15.080
Can any one nation be quite so abysmal--'

625
01:03:15.124 --> 01:03:17.393
- 'What is this nonsense? '
- 'Or is it just simply

626
01:03:17.493 --> 01:03:19.429
- that you are not here? '
- 'Do not expect me

627
01:03:19.529 --> 01:03:21.264
to sigh for your woes.

628
01:03:21.364 --> 01:03:24.567
If everything truly is as it is
more than you say.

629
01:03:24.667 --> 01:03:26.869
- then heed my simple remedy.'
- 'Frederick--'

630
01:03:26.969 --> 01:03:28.971
- 'Return at once--'
- 'darling.

631
01:03:29.071 --> 01:03:31.130
I long for your touch.

632
01:03:31.174 --> 01:03:33.109
I still seek your scent on my clothes.'

633
01:03:33.209 --> 01:03:35.803
'Come to me now.
I will free you.

634
01:03:35.845 --> 01:03:37.780
I should have pinned you to the mattress

635
01:03:37.880 --> 01:03:41.084
when last I had the chance.
Like you were the butterfly.

636
01:03:41.184 --> 01:03:43.184
I was the pin.'

637
01:03:43.219 --> 01:03:46.322
'...embroidered together.
heart against heart.'

638
01:03:46.422 --> 01:03:48.422
'Victoria. listen.

639
01:03:48.457 --> 01:03:50.693
our moment is dying...
What is this nonsense...?

640
01:03:50.793 --> 01:03:52.762
The music has come...
Like you were the butterfly...

641
01:03:52.862 --> 01:03:56.696
Everything precious is passing. my love...

642
01:03:56.732 --> 01:03:59.758
For everything I said to you

643
01:03:59.802 --> 01:04:01.904
and everything I might ever say
could be contained

644
01:04:02.004 --> 01:04:05.667
in these two words--

645
01:04:05.708 --> 01:04:08.142
come back. Victoria.

646
01:04:08.177 --> 01:04:10.236
Come back.'

647
01:04:10.279 --> 01:04:13.737
Do not write to me anymore. love.

648
01:04:37.506 --> 01:04:40.270
Ladies and gentlemen.

649
01:04:40.309 --> 01:04:43.870
thank you for your patience and understanding.

650
01:04:43.913 --> 01:04:45.748
Unfortunately.

651
01:04:45.848 --> 01:04:48.112
I have just received notice

652
01:04:48.150 --> 01:04:51.711
that Mr. Pope has been...

653
01:04:51.754 --> 01:04:54.245
afflicted by an illness.

654
01:04:56.058 --> 01:04:58.058
and unfortunately.

655
01:04:58.094 --> 01:05:00.892
cannot be with us today.

656
01:05:00.930 --> 01:05:04.627
Of course. we will refund those who desire.

657
01:05:04.667 --> 01:05:07.158
but for those who do stay.

658
01:05:07.203 --> 01:05:09.539
we are pleased to play my arrangement

659
01:05:09.639 --> 01:05:13.405
of favorite English madrigals.

660
01:05:30.760 --> 01:05:34.218
'Darling Frederick.
I have seen the truth at last.

661
01:05:34.263 --> 01:05:36.833
Eternity has passed since we were parted.

662
01:05:36.933 --> 01:05:38.868
One full week without your letters

663
01:05:38.968 --> 01:05:41.571
and I am shriveling here
like a flower in the desert.

664
01:05:41.671 --> 01:05:44.139
I will not suffer more.

665
01:05:44.173 --> 01:05:46.275
I'm not reading. as well as not writing

666
01:05:46.375 --> 01:05:48.678
and you'll miss this crucial report.

667
01:05:48.778 --> 01:05:50.778
I'm coming back. my love.

668
01:05:50.780 --> 01:05:53.950
by any means I can.
tomorrow morning if I'm able.

669
01:05:54.050 --> 01:05:57.019
And then. will you forgive me. my love?

670
01:05:57.053 --> 01:06:00.284
The wasted time.
my selfish folly.

671
01:06:00.323 --> 01:06:02.425
Will you take me in your arms again?

672
01:06:02.525 --> 01:06:04.525
And with one kiss eradicate

673
01:06:04.560 --> 01:06:07.324
each hour apart from your embrace.

674
01:06:11.033 --> 01:06:13.399
I long for you. love.

675
01:06:13.436 --> 01:06:17.338
I long for your touch and constant heart.

676
01:06:17.373 --> 01:06:19.373
Victoria.'

677
01:07:20.503 --> 01:07:22.204
Savage!

678
01:07:22.304 --> 01:07:24.499
Extreme. rude. cruel.

679
01:07:24.540 --> 01:07:27.634
- Oh. not to trust.
- Victoria.

680
01:07:27.676 --> 01:07:29.478
- You sluttish muse.
- Who is she?

681
01:07:29.578 --> 01:07:31.414
- Quiet!
- Victoria. please.

682
01:07:31.514 --> 01:07:33.573
Don't try to explain.

683
01:07:33.616 --> 01:07:35.675
It's not your fault.

684
01:07:35.718 --> 01:07:37.718
Or yours.

685
01:07:38.421 --> 01:07:41.322
Victoria.
Listen.

686
01:07:54.737 --> 01:07:56.967
'Do not despair. Victoria.

687
01:07:57.006 --> 01:08:00.305
This is the last page of our correspondence.

688
01:08:00.342 --> 01:08:03.879
I'm only writing to let you know
of my plans for suicide.

689
01:08:03.979 --> 01:08:07.676
by poison or drowning.
I have yet to decide.

690
01:08:07.716 --> 01:08:10.412
All my estate I'm leaving to you.

691
01:08:10.453 --> 01:08:13.189
I have some personal debts
that I intend to honor

692
01:08:13.289 --> 01:08:15.992
but everything else
will be yours to dispose of.

693
01:08:16.092 --> 01:08:18.322
Do with it what you will.

694
01:08:18.360 --> 01:08:20.360
It matters little to me.

695
01:08:21.263 --> 01:08:23.356
Regretfully yours.

696
01:08:23.399 --> 01:08:24.800
Frederick.'

697
01:08:24.900 --> 01:08:26.900
I'm dying.

698
01:08:27.570 --> 01:08:29.438
I'm dying.

699
01:08:29.538 --> 01:08:31.440
Do you know anything about music?

700
01:08:31.540 --> 01:08:33.442
Have you heard of Frederick Pope?
Lord Frederick Pope.

701
01:08:33.542 --> 01:08:35.177
composer. genius.

702
01:08:35.277 --> 01:08:37.980
The only goddamn virtuoso
that the nation of England

703
01:08:38.080 --> 01:08:39.815
ever came up with.

704
01:08:39.915 --> 01:08:43.078
In a few minutes.
his violin is gonna be sold

705
01:08:43.119 --> 01:08:45.087
and if I don't get there
because of your driving

706
01:08:45.187 --> 01:08:47.187
or this goddamn traffic.

707
01:08:47.223 --> 01:08:49.158
I'm going to lose my precious testicles.

708
01:08:49.258 --> 01:08:52.625
Do you understand?
I'm going to be castrated.

709
01:08:52.661 --> 01:08:55.459
Please hurry.

710
01:08:55.498 --> 01:08:57.523
It's there. Duval's.

711
01:08:57.967 --> 01:09:00.367
That's it?

712
01:09:00.402 --> 01:09:03.565
Why didn't you tell me?

713
01:09:03.606 --> 01:09:05.606
I need a receipt.

714
01:09:07.009 --> 01:09:09.409
Hello.
Nicholas Olsberg.

715
01:09:09.445 --> 01:09:11.913
- I'm late.
- Yes. you are.

716
01:09:11.947 --> 01:09:14.187
Please don't let me forget this.

717
01:09:14.950 --> 01:09:17.441
Olsberg. Nicholas.

718
01:09:17.486 --> 01:09:20.182
I registered by telephone.

719
01:09:20.222 --> 01:09:22.918
Check again under Pope Foundation.

720
01:09:22.958 --> 01:09:24.958
Pope.

721
01:09:25.761 --> 01:09:28.097
The last violin of Niccolò Bussotti--

722
01:09:28.197 --> 01:09:30.647
Here we are.
Please sign.

723
01:09:34.336 --> 01:09:36.172
There you are.

724
01:09:36.272 --> 01:09:38.900
Here she is now.
lot number 72.

725
01:09:38.941 --> 01:09:42.206
the so-called Red Violin.

726
01:09:42.244 --> 01:09:45.407
The last order bid is at $250.000.

727
01:09:45.447 --> 01:09:48.939
So we'll open the floor
and who will start us off?

728
01:09:48.984 --> 01:09:51.320
260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

729
01:09:51.420 --> 01:09:53.355
270.000.
Suzanne here on the telephone.

730
01:09:53.455 --> 01:09:54.990
280.000.
Back to you. sir.

731
01:09:55.090 --> 01:09:57.526
300.000 at the back of the room.
thank you.

732
01:09:57.626 --> 01:09:59.958
320.000.
Suzanne. I see you.

733
01:09:59.995 --> 01:10:03.522
400.000 at the back of the hall.
400.000--

734
01:13:43.419 --> 01:13:45.478
Darling. come here.

735
01:13:50.125 --> 01:13:52.125
Do you like it?

736
01:13:59.768 --> 01:14:01.768
Justice...

737
01:14:04.206 --> 01:14:06.206
There will be a trial.

738
01:14:06.241 --> 01:14:08.607
A great trial...

739
01:14:08.644 --> 01:14:11.613
before a powerful magistrate.

740
01:14:11.647 --> 01:14:13.774
And you-- you will be guilty.

741
01:14:15.284 --> 01:14:17.086
Beware!

742
01:14:17.186 --> 01:14:19.186
Beware the heat of the fire!

743
01:14:20.656 --> 01:14:22.715

744
01:15:26.288 --> 01:15:30.782
Comrade Chan Gong has come from Beijing.

745
01:15:30.826 --> 01:15:33.693
Welcome her. please.

746
01:15:47.109 --> 01:15:49.109
Comrades. students.

747
01:15:49.111 --> 01:15:52.103
revolutionary companions-in-arms...

748
01:15:52.147 --> 01:15:56.880
I give you my proletarian salute.

749
01:16:02.658 --> 01:16:05.786
I congratulate you on today's grand festival

750
01:16:05.827 --> 01:16:08.625
for which you have worked so hard.

751
01:16:08.664 --> 01:16:12.225
Your cultural unit has done exceptional work.

752
01:16:17.072 --> 01:16:22.704
I would also commend you
on the children's presentation.

753
01:16:22.744 --> 01:16:25.907
It made my heart rejoice.

754
01:16:25.948 --> 01:16:28.317
The story of 'The Three Heroic Girls'

755
01:16:28.417 --> 01:16:30.510
was a vivid lesson.

756
01:16:30.552 --> 01:16:35.353
It galvanized our historic crusade!

757
01:16:35.390 --> 01:16:39.759
But unfortunately. some efforts

758
01:16:39.795 --> 01:16:42.286
are less successful.

759
01:16:44.299 --> 01:16:47.564
Sometimes the teacher must learn

760
01:16:47.603 --> 01:16:49.764
from his students.

761
01:16:53.508 --> 01:16:55.508
Give it to me.

762
01:17:02.951 --> 01:17:06.910
Capitalist exploitation survived for centuries

763
01:17:06.955 --> 01:17:09.583
yet its 'classics' are pitiful.

764
01:17:09.625 --> 01:17:14.392
Foreign music is meaningless and empty.

765
01:17:14.429 --> 01:17:17.065
What do they mean by 'symphony.' 'concerto.'

766
01:17:17.165 --> 01:17:19.861
'No 1.' 'No 2.' 'No 3'?

767
01:17:19.901 --> 01:17:23.639
This is empty formalism.
It speaks nothing to the people.

768
01:17:23.739 --> 01:17:26.936
What good is making music

769
01:17:26.975 --> 01:17:31.412
except to teach and inspire the people?

770
01:17:31.446 --> 01:17:33.505
Long live Chairman Mao!

771
01:17:35.317 --> 01:17:37.907
Overthrow the cultural establishment!

772
01:17:41.890 --> 01:17:42.758
Chou Yuan?

773
01:17:42.858 --> 01:17:43.825
Present.

774
01:17:43.925 --> 01:17:46.587
Why do you teach this instrument?

775
01:17:50.032 --> 01:17:53.195
Comrade Chan Gong.
what you say is true--

776
01:17:53.235 --> 01:17:55.235
Louder. please.

777
01:17:57.839 --> 01:18:00.865
Comrade Chan Gong.
you are right.

778
01:18:00.909 --> 01:18:03.139
Much of Western music

779
01:18:03.178 --> 01:18:05.178
is unrefined. worthless.

780
01:18:05.180 --> 01:18:07.671
This is a fact.

781
01:18:07.716 --> 01:18:12.153
Everything you said is true.
but the music I teach--

782
01:18:12.187 --> 01:18:13.889
Go on!

783
01:18:13.989 --> 01:18:17.049
The music I teach is revolutionary music--

784
01:18:17.092 --> 01:18:19.287
Beethoven. Prokofiev--

785
01:18:19.327 --> 01:18:21.327
Do you think so?

786
01:18:21.897 --> 01:18:24.229
In his speech.
Comrade Li said--

787
01:18:24.266 --> 01:18:27.463
Comrade Li was purged and humiliated.

788
01:18:27.502 --> 01:18:29.502
Do you wish to quote him?

789
01:18:30.872 --> 01:18:34.399
I didn't know.

790
01:18:34.443 --> 01:18:36.968
I have taught for many years.

791
01:18:37.012 --> 01:18:38.714
That is apparent.

792
01:18:38.814 --> 01:18:41.783
We believe in the rule of many voices.

793
01:18:41.817 --> 01:18:43.685
What should we do here?

794
01:18:43.785 --> 01:18:46.083
Throw away that old junk!

795
01:18:46.121 --> 01:18:48.715
Chou Yuan you must admit your guilt.

796
01:18:48.757 --> 01:18:51.487
Let's challenge degenerate Western art!

797
01:18:52.227 --> 01:18:54.821
Comrade. may I say a few words?

798
01:18:57.432 --> 01:18:59.432
Of course.

799
01:19:00.569 --> 01:19:05.006
Students. comrades.
revolutionary Red Guards...

800
01:19:06.575 --> 01:19:10.204
I'm not an authority on foreign music.

801
01:19:10.245 --> 01:19:12.814
I have not studied like Comrade Chan Gong.

802
01:19:12.914 --> 01:19:15.178
But in my opinion

803
01:19:15.217 --> 01:19:18.927
there's nothing as beautiful
as our traditional music.

804
01:19:19.621 --> 01:19:22.071
Chou Yuan also teaches the hu chin.

805
01:19:22.891 --> 01:19:24.891
Could he not focus on that?

806
01:19:33.034 --> 01:19:35.798
Comrade Xiang has shown her wisdom.

807
01:19:42.911 --> 01:19:47.678
Put this down with the other 'great olds'!

808
01:19:56.458 --> 01:19:59.723
To every problem there is a solution!

809
01:19:59.761 --> 01:20:02.559
I'm sure you can discover the problems.

810
01:20:02.597 --> 01:20:05.464
And I'm sure that you can solve them.

811
01:20:24.386 --> 01:20:26.386

812
01:22:59.240 --> 01:23:01.240

813
01:23:01.509 --> 01:23:03.509
Who's there?

814
01:23:03.711 --> 01:23:05.711
Who is it?

815
01:23:06.281 --> 01:23:08.875
Who's there?

816
01:23:11.619 --> 01:23:13.087
Ming!

817
01:23:13.187 --> 01:23:15.451
You scared me.
I didn't hear you.

818
01:23:24.866 --> 01:23:27.334
It's a mess.
I was tidying up.

819
01:23:27.368 --> 01:23:29.529
What's that?

820
01:23:32.173 --> 01:23:34.173
This is a violin--

821
01:23:35.143 --> 01:23:37.475
a musical instrument from Europe.

822
01:23:37.512 --> 01:23:38.913
- From Europe?
- Yes.

823
01:23:39.013 --> 01:23:40.248
Is it a bad thing?

824
01:23:40.348 --> 01:23:44.978
No. A violin itself is a good thing.

825
01:23:45.019 --> 01:23:47.681
Here. Take a look.

826
01:23:51.159 --> 01:23:54.329
We have to study foreign music
so we can move on

827
01:23:54.429 --> 01:23:56.454
as Chairman Mao said.

828
01:23:56.497 --> 01:23:58.590
Dad asked if you're coming.

829
01:23:58.633 --> 01:24:00.168
He's waiting.

830
01:24:00.268 --> 01:24:03.567
Yes. Tell him I'll come to see him right away.

831
01:24:03.604 --> 01:24:05.774
As soon as I finish my... work.

832
01:24:09.277 --> 01:24:12.371
- Ming?
- Yes?

833
01:24:13.681 --> 01:24:18.983
What you see here-- don't tell anyone.

834
01:24:25.059 --> 01:24:27.059
I want you to listen.

835
01:25:21.349 --> 01:25:23.729
This will be our secret.
all right?

836
01:25:28.756 --> 01:25:30.756
Go.

837
01:25:55.817 --> 01:25:57.817
Ming!

838
01:26:00.288 --> 01:26:02.288
- Was she home?
- Yes.

839
01:26:02.290 --> 01:26:06.454
- Is she coming?
- No. She said she'd meet you.

840
01:26:06.494 --> 01:26:08.587
What? Is she coming or not?

841
01:26:08.629 --> 01:26:11.223
- I can't say why.
- Why what?

842
01:26:11.265 --> 01:26:13.401
I promised her to keep it secret.

843
01:26:13.501 --> 01:26:15.503
What are you saying?
I'm your father.

844
01:26:15.603 --> 01:26:18.333
You must tell me everything.

845
01:26:25.580 --> 01:26:27.115
- Xiang Pei!
- Papa. don't!

846
01:26:27.215 --> 01:26:30.309
Open up. It's me.

847
01:26:30.351 --> 01:26:32.581
Where's the key?

848
01:26:32.620 --> 01:26:34.620
Go!

849
01:26:43.831 --> 01:26:45.831
Quiet!

850
01:26:54.642 --> 01:26:56.642
Where is she?

851
01:27:01.549 --> 01:27:03.549
Water! Water!

852
01:27:16.797 --> 01:27:18.797
She's gone!

853
01:27:55.536 --> 01:27:57.536
Is this her?

854
01:28:03.477 --> 01:28:07.538
Look at the date: 1937.
It must be her mother.

855
01:28:29.003 --> 01:28:31.003
Chou Yuan!

856
01:28:31.238 --> 01:28:33.238
Chou Yuan!

857
01:28:34.542 --> 01:28:36.542
Chou Yuan!

858
01:28:44.885 --> 01:28:46.721
- What do you want?
- Please let me in.

859
01:28:46.821 --> 01:28:48.589
I've done nothing.

860
01:28:48.689 --> 01:28:50.689
Let me inside.

861
01:29:04.005 --> 01:29:07.497
- This is for you.
- I don't want it.

862
01:29:17.385 --> 01:29:19.979
It's for you. Take it.

863
01:29:21.889 --> 01:29:23.889
It's a violin.

864
01:29:24.425 --> 01:29:27.792
- A violin.
- I remember.

865
01:29:30.231 --> 01:29:32.631
Do you want it or not?

866
01:29:32.667 --> 01:29:34.936
I'm an old man.
but I'm not a fool.

867
01:29:35.036 --> 01:29:38.028
Where are your comrades?

868
01:29:38.072 --> 01:29:40.336
Are they waiting outside?

869
01:29:40.374 --> 01:29:41.976
This isn't a trap.

870
01:29:42.076 --> 01:29:43.177
I've changed.

871
01:29:43.277 --> 01:29:46.337
I don't need it now.
I speak from my heart.

872
01:29:46.380 --> 01:29:48.380
Enough!

873
01:29:50.051 --> 01:29:53.384
And I don't need this.

874
01:29:53.421 --> 01:29:57.255
It's from another time.

875
01:29:57.291 --> 01:30:00.556
If you want it.
you can have it

876
01:30:00.594 --> 01:30:03.324
or else no one will.

877
01:30:05.433 --> 01:30:07.697
Do you want it or not?

878
01:30:10.504 --> 01:30:12.504
I've no time!

879
01:30:13.574 --> 01:30:15.701
No more arguments.

880
01:30:18.379 --> 01:30:20.609
Take it!

881
01:30:23.017 --> 01:30:27.078
I am a cadre in the Party.
Do you understand?

882
01:30:27.121 --> 01:30:29.817
I can't keep it.

883
01:30:29.857 --> 01:30:33.987
I love the people.
Do you understand?

884
01:30:49.210 --> 01:30:51.210
Xiang Pei!

885
01:30:54.381 --> 01:30:56.440
I will keep it safe.

886
01:31:05.693 --> 01:31:08.184
Let's go eat.
I'm starving.

887
01:31:08.229 --> 01:31:12.825
Go ahead. I'll wait here.
I'm sure she'll be back.

888
01:31:12.867 --> 01:31:14.867

889
01:31:34.054 --> 01:31:36.682
Auctioneer:...$1.950.000.

890
01:31:36.724 --> 01:31:40.626
And sold to the lady on my left.

891
01:31:40.661 --> 01:31:44.028
The last sale of the evening.
lot number 72.

892
01:31:44.064 --> 01:31:47.134
on the turntable there.
The star of the night--

893
01:31:47.234 --> 01:31:48.569
where is she?

894
01:31:48.669 --> 01:31:53.038
The last violin of Niccolò Bussotti. 1 681.

895
01:31:53.073 --> 01:31:55.342
- A masterpiece of the--
- Do you see it?

896
01:31:55.442 --> 01:31:56.644
No. not yet.

897
01:31:56.744 --> 01:31:59.054
If she will give us the pleasure.

898
01:32:00.381 --> 01:32:03.214
And here she is now.
lot number 72.

899
01:32:03.250 --> 01:32:06.185
the so-called Red Violin.

900
01:32:06.220 --> 01:32:10.316
- And the last order bid--
- Not at all how I remember it.

901
01:32:10.357 --> 01:32:12.993
They've cleaned it up
and fixed it. It's better.

902
01:32:13.093 --> 01:32:16.187
260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

903
01:32:16.230 --> 01:32:18.032
270.000.
Suzanne on the telephones.

904
01:32:18.132 --> 01:32:21.202
- Maybe if I heard it again.
- 280.000. Back to you. sir.

905
01:32:21.302 --> 01:32:22.970
300.000 at the back of the hall.

906
01:32:23.070 --> 01:32:24.939
320.000.
Suzanne. I see you.

907
01:32:25.039 --> 01:32:26.674
340.000.
I have you here.

908
01:32:26.774 --> 01:32:29.994
- 380.000. Mr. Ruselsky.
- The last card.

909
01:32:31.445 --> 01:32:33.445
The last card.

910
01:32:41.222 --> 01:32:44.453
- Oh. my God!
- Courage. madame.

911
01:32:44.491 --> 01:32:46.360
Upside down.

912
01:32:46.460 --> 01:32:49.122
At this point in the spread

913
01:32:49.163 --> 01:32:51.654
it might be good news.

914
01:32:54.468 --> 01:32:56.468
I feel--

915
01:32:56.971 --> 01:33:00.600
I feel the fast air sweeping around you...

916
01:33:00.641 --> 01:33:03.201
carrying you--

917
01:33:03.244 --> 01:33:06.008
furious wind--

918
01:33:06.046 --> 01:33:08.046
and then stopping.

919
01:33:15.489 --> 01:33:20.290
Your journey will end.
No question. I see it.

920
01:33:20.327 --> 01:33:24.696
One way or another.
your travels are over.

921
01:33:27.434 --> 01:33:31.131
And there is trouble in this--

922
01:33:31.171 --> 01:33:33.171
like always.

923
01:33:35.576 --> 01:33:37.278
But you--

924
01:33:37.378 --> 01:33:39.642
you are strong by now--

925
01:33:39.680 --> 01:33:43.172
strong like a tree in the forest.

926
01:33:43.217 --> 01:33:45.549
Where is he?

927
01:33:45.586 --> 01:33:47.586
Upstairs.

928
01:33:54.361 --> 01:33:56.096
You are not alone.

929
01:33:56.196 --> 01:34:00.758
A crowd of faces.
friends and family.

930
01:34:00.801 --> 01:34:03.770
enemies. lovers.

931
01:34:03.804 --> 01:34:07.467
You will attract many admirers

932
01:34:07.508 --> 01:34:09.874
fighting to win your hand.

933
01:34:11.345 --> 01:34:12.813
And money--

934
01:34:12.913 --> 01:34:15.040
Iots of money.

935
01:34:15.082 --> 01:34:16.951
No. madame.

936
01:34:17.051 --> 01:34:19.747
Don't be afraid.

937
01:34:19.787 --> 01:34:22.654
In this card I see...

938
01:34:22.690 --> 01:34:25.784
I see...

939
01:34:25.826 --> 01:34:28.659
a rebirth.

940
01:34:30.030 --> 01:34:32.933
- And how was your flight?
- Very good. On time.

941
01:34:33.033 --> 01:34:34.969
Sorry to cut your holiday short.

942
01:34:35.069 --> 01:34:37.004
It's quite all right.
I'm excited actually.

943
01:34:37.104 --> 01:34:39.039
- Like Christmas.
- It won't take too long.

944
01:34:39.139 --> 01:34:41.275
We already divided them up and assessed them.

945
01:34:41.375 --> 01:34:42.977
- Right. Ballpark.
- And all that they want

946
01:34:43.077 --> 01:34:44.979
- is for you to confirm it.
- I got it.

947
01:34:45.079 --> 01:34:46.013
A second opinion.

948
01:34:46.113 --> 01:34:48.048
I've done this sort of thing before.

949
01:34:48.148 --> 01:34:50.248
Can't wait to see it.
actually.

950
01:34:52.286 --> 01:34:54.386
This is Mr. Morritz.
You know--

951
01:34:56.824 --> 01:34:58.525
So. you're the expert?

952
01:34:58.625 --> 01:35:01.059
From New York.

953
01:35:01.095 --> 01:35:03.495
Do you know what you're doing?

954
01:35:03.530 --> 01:35:05.199
Yes. New York.

955
01:35:05.299 --> 01:35:06.700
Do you know what you're doing?

956
01:35:06.800 --> 01:35:07.701
Oh.

957
01:35:07.801 --> 01:35:10.292
Why yes.
I certainly hope so.

958
01:35:10.337 --> 01:35:12.606
These people from Duval's
have given us some figures

959
01:35:12.706 --> 01:35:16.540
and we have figures from
the government of China.

960
01:35:16.577 --> 01:35:18.577
What we need now is--

961
01:35:18.579 --> 01:35:20.579
Professional opinion.

962
01:35:20.614 --> 01:35:22.614
No. a signed affidavit.

963
01:35:22.649 --> 01:35:24.649
That's what I'm here for.

964
01:35:24.685 --> 01:35:26.744
Show me to the Strad.

965
01:35:26.787 --> 01:35:29.623
- They all look the same to me.
- But they're not.

966
01:35:29.723 --> 01:35:31.592
Please don't let me forget this.

967
01:35:31.692 --> 01:35:33.717
Over there.

968
01:35:40.501 --> 01:35:42.935
Here she is.

969
01:35:42.970 --> 01:35:44.970
It's a beautiful specimen.

970
01:35:48.242 --> 01:35:50.676
I'd say about...

971
01:35:50.711 --> 01:35:53.976
1683.

972
01:35:54.014 --> 01:35:55.549
Reminds me of the Cobet.

973
01:35:55.649 --> 01:35:57.785
These are the best quality pieces we found.

974
01:35:57.885 --> 01:35:59.053
And here--

975
01:35:59.153 --> 01:36:01.755
over here. if you'd like to take a look.

976
01:36:01.855 --> 01:36:03.390
are the less promising entries.

977
01:36:03.490 --> 01:36:05.490
Some of them are pretty bad.

978
01:36:07.995 --> 01:36:10.486
So I see.

979
01:36:10.531 --> 01:36:12.166
I guess I'll leave it to you.

980
01:36:12.266 --> 01:36:16.532
I've taken care of the luggage.
I have a driver waiting.

981
01:36:16.570 --> 01:36:18.570
I shouldn't be long.

982
01:36:51.572 --> 01:36:53.707
- Bonjour.
- Bonjour. Mr. Morritz.

983
01:36:53.807 --> 01:36:56.010
Everything is ready as you asked for. I hope.

984
01:36:56.110 --> 01:36:58.278
- Same room as always?
- We have the same room

985
01:36:58.378 --> 01:37:00.047
but one story down.

986
01:37:00.147 --> 01:37:02.082
If it's not the same floor.
it's not the same room. is it?

987
01:37:02.182 --> 01:37:04.518
No. sir. But it's the same as the other one.

988
01:37:04.618 --> 01:37:07.485
Oh. sir.
I have a message from your wife.

989
01:37:07.521 --> 01:37:09.521
Merci.

990
01:37:19.766 --> 01:37:22.462
Room 2703.

991
01:37:22.503 --> 01:37:24.562
New York City. please.

992
01:37:25.672 --> 01:37:28.368
316-2799.

993
01:37:31.945 --> 01:37:34.311
Carrie. Charles Morritz here.

994
01:37:34.348 --> 01:37:37.451
I have a little gumshoe work
I need you to get onto.

995
01:37:37.551 --> 01:37:39.746
Cremona. Bussotti.

996
01:37:39.786 --> 01:37:41.786
Get a pen.

997
01:37:47.194 --> 01:37:50.204
Made a cast of this after we set the table.

998
01:37:51.598 --> 01:37:53.333
The Swiss--

999
01:37:53.433 --> 01:37:54.501
so here we are.

1000
01:37:54.601 --> 01:37:56.831
Here's the before picture.

1001
01:37:56.870 --> 01:37:58.072
Take a look at the corners.

1002
01:37:58.172 --> 01:38:00.441
Not too bad. I don't think
we have to touch them.

1003
01:38:00.541 --> 01:38:02.907
Some really nice purfling here.

1004
01:38:04.878 --> 01:38:06.713
A lot of work to get it this far.

1005
01:38:06.813 --> 01:38:09.049
Turn-of-the-century hack job
with some horse glue

1006
01:38:09.149 --> 01:38:11.285
and a patch.
so I had to reset the neck.

1007
01:38:11.385 --> 01:38:14.718
That was the big job.
Sound post. tailpiece.

1008
01:38:14.755 --> 01:38:16.924
new bridge. of course.
But the body itself

1009
01:38:17.024 --> 01:38:19.893
is remarkably good.
I'm just gonna clean it up.

1010
01:38:19.993 --> 01:38:23.053
- strip back some varnish--
- No. no. No.

1011
01:38:23.096 --> 01:38:24.064
No what?

1012
01:38:24.164 --> 01:38:27.725
I told you before.
don't touch the varnish.

1013
01:38:27.768 --> 01:38:30.604
- That's not gonna be easy.
- If there's a problem.

1014
01:38:30.704 --> 01:38:32.704
I'll do it myself.

1015
01:38:34.308 --> 01:38:36.776
Look. the auction's in two weeks.

1016
01:38:36.810 --> 01:38:38.812
I have 1 6 other instruments.
Leroux's all over my ass.

1017
01:38:38.912 --> 01:38:40.948
I still have a Steiner I haven't even touched.

1018
01:38:41.048 --> 01:38:43.250
I want complete LIGs.
a resonance test.

1019
01:38:43.350 --> 01:38:46.153
mass specs and let's get some varnish samples

1020
01:38:46.253 --> 01:38:48.687
all to the lab. okay?

1021
01:38:50.324 --> 01:38:53.020
This instrument is not a priority.

1022
01:38:53.060 --> 01:38:55.255
Every minute of my day is full.

1023
01:38:55.295 --> 01:38:56.797
That's fine.

1024
01:38:56.897 --> 01:38:59.417
We'll do this after hours.
all right?

1025
01:39:06.940 --> 01:39:10.205
- These are the estimates?
- No. the reserves.

1026
01:39:10.244 --> 01:39:12.012
That we propose to the Chinese?

1027
01:39:12.112 --> 01:39:16.071
- Right.
- And what about these?

1028
01:39:16.116 --> 01:39:18.051
Those are some contentious items

1029
01:39:18.151 --> 01:39:20.087
you might not want to put on the block.

1030
01:39:20.187 --> 01:39:23.407
They're badly preserved and hard to attribute.

1031
01:39:23.790 --> 01:39:26.020
What about that red one?

1032
01:39:26.059 --> 01:39:27.327
The red one?

1033
01:39:27.427 --> 01:39:30.647
Leroux seemed to think it might be a Bussotti.

1034
01:39:32.199 --> 01:39:34.394
Yes.

1035
01:39:34.434 --> 01:39:35.936
It might be.

1036
01:39:36.036 --> 01:39:39.006
But the label's obscure and the varnish is odd.

1037
01:39:39.106 --> 01:39:40.841
It's slightly opaque.

1038
01:39:40.941 --> 01:39:44.604
And I'm afraid as it stands
with no documentation--

1039
01:39:44.645 --> 01:39:46.645
And that's all you expect?

1040
01:40:04.731 --> 01:40:09.065
'With all my heart.'

1041
01:40:13.040 --> 01:40:16.635
You ever heard of the Red Violin?

1042
01:40:16.677 --> 01:40:19.737
Sure. sure-- what--

1043
01:40:19.780 --> 01:40:22.816
the Frederick Pope Bussotti?
Sure. I heard stories.

1044
01:40:22.916 --> 01:40:24.751
How about copies?

1045
01:40:24.851 --> 01:40:26.853
There's one in London.
the only one I know of--

1046
01:40:26.953 --> 01:40:30.047
supposed to be copy commissioned by Pope.

1047
01:40:30.090 --> 01:40:33.787
- You know who has it?
- Some private collection.

1048
01:40:34.961 --> 01:40:39.864
You think I could...
buy it without tipping them off?

1049
01:40:39.900 --> 01:40:42.664
Tipping them off to what?

1050
01:40:42.703 --> 01:40:44.638
We know for sure we have a Bussotti.

1051
01:40:44.738 --> 01:40:46.073
I can date it within the year.

1052
01:40:46.173 --> 01:40:49.076
We still have this varnish
that doesn't configure

1053
01:40:49.176 --> 01:40:51.111
but we run some comparison tests

1054
01:40:51.211 --> 01:40:54.305
and see if this is the source of the copy.

1055
01:40:57.084 --> 01:41:00.576
You know I should probably tell my employer?

1056
01:41:00.620 --> 01:41:02.823
If what you're saying is any way true

1057
01:41:02.923 --> 01:41:06.188
people could get a little...
excited.

1058
01:41:06.226 --> 01:41:08.428
You know I could lose my job over this?

1059
01:41:08.528 --> 01:41:11.520
Yes. I know.

1060
01:41:11.565 --> 01:41:13.863
You can go if you want to.

1061
01:41:13.900 --> 01:41:15.900
I can finish this myself.

1062
01:41:40.193 --> 01:41:44.393
Madame Leroux says that she has
to have catalog proofs today.

1063
01:41:45.766 --> 01:41:47.467
Are you finished?

1064
01:41:47.567 --> 01:41:50.195
Yes. they're back at my hotel.

1065
01:41:50.237 --> 01:41:52.237
I've been working at night.

1066
01:41:54.941 --> 01:41:56.941
Is there something else?

1067
01:41:56.977 --> 01:41:58.977
Oh.

1068
01:41:59.613 --> 01:42:02.946
Your wife called again.

1069
01:42:02.983 --> 01:42:05.042
Close the door. please.

1070
01:42:14.961 --> 01:42:17.987
Yes. is this the University of Montreal?

1071
01:42:18.031 --> 01:42:21.181
May I have the archeology department. please?

1072
01:42:24.771 --> 01:42:28.104
Hi. this is Charles Morritz over at Duval's.

1073
01:42:28.141 --> 01:42:31.151
I sent you some varnish samples on Tuesday.

1074
01:42:32.712 --> 01:42:36.142
Yeah. I wanted you
to isolate an organic compound.

1075
01:43:01.007 --> 01:43:03.007

1076
01:43:06.546 --> 01:43:08.546

1077
01:43:12.052 --> 01:43:14.052

1078
01:43:14.821 --> 01:43:16.821
Excuse me.

1079
01:43:21.595 --> 01:43:24.223
May I have the manager. please?

1080
01:43:24.264 --> 01:43:26.391
Yes. the manager.

1081
01:43:26.433 --> 01:43:28.433
Well fine. put him on.

1082
01:43:30.504 --> 01:43:34.270
Yes. this is Mr. Morritz in 2703.

1083
01:43:34.307 --> 01:43:36.977
Listen. I want to make something
absolutely clear.

1084
01:43:37.077 --> 01:43:39.413
I don't want anyone coming to my room.

1085
01:43:39.513 --> 01:43:40.447
You understand?

1086
01:43:40.547 --> 01:43:43.448
Not the maid.
Not to check the minibar.

1087
01:43:43.483 --> 01:43:45.483
No chocolates on the pillow.

1088
01:43:45.519 --> 01:43:48.755
I'm giving your staff
sort of a break. understand?

1089
01:43:48.855 --> 01:43:51.119
No one is to come in my room

1090
01:43:51.157 --> 01:43:53.157
unless I request it.

1091
01:43:54.261 --> 01:43:56.261
Thank you.

1092
01:44:11.511 --> 01:44:13.511

1093
01:44:16.483 --> 01:44:19.145
- Yes.
- I got it.

1094
01:44:19.185 --> 01:44:21.915
It's coming.
I just talked to London.

1095
01:44:21.955 --> 01:44:23.890
Well. you know.
a little bit of smooth talk

1096
01:44:23.990 --> 01:44:26.720
and a little bit more money.
Your money.

1097
01:44:27.961 --> 01:44:30.341
You better make those phone calls.

1098
01:44:31.765 --> 01:44:34.962
Yeah. yeah. yeah.
me too.

1099
01:44:35.001 --> 01:44:37.367
Well. actually--

1100
01:44:51.051 --> 01:44:53.051
- Wonderful.
- Yes.

1101
01:44:53.086 --> 01:44:55.145
I have the recording.

1102
01:44:55.188 --> 01:44:57.123
Pretty good Strad.
don't you think?

1103
01:44:57.223 --> 01:44:59.392
I feel a little bit tight on the top.

1104
01:44:59.492 --> 01:45:02.427
A little bit stronger over the break.

1105
01:45:02.462 --> 01:45:05.920
To me it's very clean.
precise.

1106
01:45:05.966 --> 01:45:09.697
Of course. it would
have to be played by a master.

1107
01:45:09.736 --> 01:45:11.304
What do you guess?

1108
01:45:11.404 --> 01:45:15.101
- 1.7. 1.8 million.
- Not bad.

1109
01:45:15.141 --> 01:45:17.744
- Trust me on this.
- What else do you have?

1110
01:45:17.844 --> 01:45:20.380
That's about it.
But thanks for coming.

1111
01:45:20.480 --> 01:45:22.549
I hope you don't have an orchestra waiting.

1112
01:45:22.649 --> 01:45:25.914
They can wait.
They can wait. no problem.

1113
01:45:28.188 --> 01:45:30.850
What about this here?

1114
01:45:30.890 --> 01:45:34.087
No. not that one.

1115
01:45:34.127 --> 01:45:38.086
- Nice little piece.
- But not for you.

1116
01:45:39.432 --> 01:45:42.560
- I will try it.
- No. no. no. Don't play it.

1117
01:45:42.602 --> 01:45:44.729
- Why not?
- Yes. why not?

1118
01:45:44.771 --> 01:45:47.641
I've just repaired it.
It's still fragile.

1119
01:45:47.641 --> 01:45:49.576
I don't even know why it's here.

1120
01:45:49.676 --> 01:45:52.611
I'll be very gentle.
Don't worry.

1121
01:46:45.765 --> 01:46:48.495
Yes. I see what you mean.

1122
01:46:48.535 --> 01:46:50.535
Nothing special.

1123
01:46:59.279 --> 01:47:01.279
How's it going?

1124
01:47:03.550 --> 01:47:06.953
What do you want me to do
with that one. the Pope copy?

1125
01:47:07.053 --> 01:47:10.079
I'll take it back to the hotel.

1126
01:47:10.123 --> 01:47:13.763
You got your money's worth.
That is a very good copy.

1127
01:47:13.793 --> 01:47:15.852
Nice violin.

1128
01:47:15.895 --> 01:47:18.728
but nothing like this one.

1129
01:47:18.765 --> 01:47:20.166
This...

1130
01:47:20.266 --> 01:47:23.758
is the single most perfect acoustic machine

1131
01:47:23.803 --> 01:47:26.135
I have ever seen.

1132
01:47:28.575 --> 01:47:30.575
Amazing.

1133
01:47:40.253 --> 01:47:42.687
Guess I never thought I'd find it.

1134
01:47:46.626 --> 01:47:50.426
The ultimate...
thing as I see it.

1135
01:47:52.499 --> 01:47:55.093
The perfect marriage

1136
01:47:55.135 --> 01:47:57.135
of science

1137
01:47:57.170 --> 01:47:59.170
and beauty.

1138
01:47:59.906 --> 01:48:01.906
Impossible.

1139
01:48:04.577 --> 01:48:06.577
Now what?

1140
01:48:07.647 --> 01:48:12.277
What do you do when the thing
you most wanted so...

1141
01:48:12.318 --> 01:48:14.154
perfect...

1142
01:48:14.254 --> 01:48:16.381
just comes?

1143
01:48:22.962 --> 01:48:24.798
Do you have children?

1144
01:48:24.898 --> 01:48:26.332
Huh?

1145
01:48:26.432 --> 01:48:28.662
Children.
You have any?

1146
01:48:28.701 --> 01:48:30.704
No. no. I don't.
but I know what you mean.

1147
01:48:30.804 --> 01:48:34.433
I would love to have this baby for myself.

1148
01:48:34.474 --> 01:48:35.875
Really?

1149
01:48:35.975 --> 01:48:38.773
What would you do?

1150
01:48:38.812 --> 01:48:42.441
Take it apart.
Find out how it works.

1151
01:48:42.482 --> 01:48:45.585
Take some igonmode readings
on the individual plates.

1152
01:48:45.685 --> 01:48:49.746
- I don't think you get it.
- Oh. yes. yes I do.

1153
01:48:49.789 --> 01:48:52.257
Take a look at this.

1154
01:48:52.292 --> 01:48:56.228
This is mode one.
.06 kHz.

1155
01:48:56.262 --> 01:48:58.662
Watch the response curve here.

1156
01:49:02.802 --> 01:49:05.168
I'll ease it up slowly for you.

1157
01:49:10.643 --> 01:49:13.237
Mode two.

1158
01:49:17.984 --> 01:49:20.145
Stop it.

1159
01:49:24.791 --> 01:49:27.225
- Bonjour. Mr. Morritz.
- Bonjour.

1160
01:49:27.260 --> 01:49:31.040
I have an envelope for you
from University of Montreal.

1161
01:49:32.532 --> 01:49:35.502
This says this arrived at 7:00.
I was in my room.

1162
01:49:35.602 --> 01:49:37.203
Yes. sir.

1163
01:49:37.303 --> 01:49:39.303
Why wasn't I notified?

1164
01:49:39.305 --> 01:49:40.640
You told us not to disturb you.

1165
01:49:40.740 --> 01:49:43.443
- Not for a courier.
- I didn't know. sir.

1166
01:49:43.543 --> 01:49:47.213
If a courier comes. you call me.
If a fax comes. you call me.

1167
01:49:47.313 --> 01:49:49.349
- Yes.
- It's important. do you get it?

1168
01:49:49.449 --> 01:49:52.051
You knock on my door and you put it in my hand.

1169
01:49:52.151 --> 01:49:54.210
Comprende?

1170
01:49:54.254 --> 01:49:56.089
I need you to acknowledge.

1171
01:49:56.189 --> 01:49:58.189
Yes.

1172
01:50:01.628 --> 01:50:03.628
This is my business!

1173
01:53:47.086 --> 01:53:48.187

1174
01:53:48.287 --> 01:53:50.881
Mr. Morritz. I'm sorry.

1175
01:53:50.923 --> 01:53:54.160
You'd better come up.
I'm-- they're waiting for you.

1176
01:53:54.260 --> 01:53:56.260
All right.

1177
01:54:00.266 --> 01:54:03.167
So nice of you to join us.

1178
01:54:03.202 --> 01:54:05.138
I hope you don't mind us starting without you.

1179
01:54:05.238 --> 01:54:07.206
but there was the question
of some unusual expenses.

1180
01:54:07.306 --> 01:54:10.298
both here in the office

1181
01:54:10.343 --> 01:54:12.343
and at the hotel.

1182
01:54:12.378 --> 01:54:15.581
- Did you check my minibar too?
- It is our card. We are paying.

1183
01:54:15.681 --> 01:54:17.617
You made me wonder what was going on down here.

1184
01:54:17.717 --> 01:54:19.852
so we decided to come down and have a look.

1185
01:54:19.952 --> 01:54:22.147
and my. you have been busy.

1186
01:54:22.188 --> 01:54:24.486
amidst the courier bills

1187
01:54:24.524 --> 01:54:26.125
and DNA tests.

1188
01:54:26.225 --> 01:54:28.225
Very curious procedures.

1189
01:54:28.261 --> 01:54:30.525
Leroux has a theory.

1190
01:54:30.563 --> 01:54:32.656
Tell me if she's wrong.

1191
01:54:38.437 --> 01:54:42.874
Is our little red violin.
'The Red Violin'?

1192
01:54:49.849 --> 01:54:50.950
Yes.

1193
01:54:51.050 --> 01:54:53.075
I just wanted to be sure

1194
01:54:53.119 --> 01:54:54.420
before I told you.

1195
01:54:54.520 --> 01:54:57.683
This is very good news.

1196
01:54:57.723 --> 01:55:00.248
I'll set up a press release.

1197
01:55:03.930 --> 01:55:06.160
Good work.

1198
01:55:06.199 --> 01:55:08.034
Thank you.

1199
01:55:08.134 --> 01:55:10.636
Why don't you take these last few days off?

1200
01:55:10.736 --> 01:55:13.170
Before you go home.

1201
01:55:18.477 --> 01:55:20.146
No.

1202
01:55:20.246 --> 01:55:22.646
No. I won't forget.

1203
01:55:23.816 --> 01:55:25.017
He lied.

1204
01:55:25.117 --> 01:55:29.451
He lied to me. And I knew it
as soon as I saw it.

1205
01:55:29.488 --> 01:55:31.615
And I said it.

1206
01:55:32.658 --> 01:55:36.059
This instrument should be mine.

1207
01:55:37.997 --> 01:55:39.997
Son of a bitch.

1208
01:56:36.856 --> 01:56:37.823
Ladies and gentlemen.

1209
01:56:37.923 --> 01:56:40.391
Duval's would like to welcome you

1210
01:56:40.426 --> 01:56:42.261
to this eagerly awaited event.

1211
01:56:42.361 --> 01:56:45.853
Our thanks to the government of China

1212
01:56:45.898 --> 01:56:49.800
for entrusting us
with this marvelous collection.

1213
01:56:49.835 --> 01:56:52.463
Thanks too to Madame Leroux.

1214
01:56:52.505 --> 01:56:56.134
who organized and made possible this auction.

1215
01:56:56.175 --> 01:56:59.576
Let me remind you that the conditions of sale

1216
01:56:59.612 --> 01:57:01.612
are listed in the catalog.

1217
01:57:01.614 --> 01:57:03.549
Before we begin. it is my duty to direct you

1218
01:57:03.649 --> 01:57:05.649
to the conditions of sale

1219
01:57:05.651 --> 01:57:07.587
that you'll find at the front of the catalog.

1220
01:57:07.687 --> 01:57:09.622
I will not read them out loud at this point

1221
01:57:09.722 --> 01:57:12.213
but consider yourselves warned.

1222
01:57:13.259 --> 01:57:15.461
Now ladies and gentlemen.
we'll begin with lot number one.

1223
01:57:15.561 --> 01:57:17.430
Showing on the turntable on my right.

1224
01:57:17.530 --> 01:57:19.623
a fine French cello.

1225
01:57:19.665 --> 01:57:22.828
I'm gonna start with $1 0.000.

1226
01:57:22.868 --> 01:57:25.132
$1 0.000.

1227
01:57:54.133 --> 01:57:56.601
- Anything else?
- No.

1228
01:57:56.635 --> 01:57:59.035
- Which airport. sir?
- Dorval.

1229
01:58:04.677 --> 01:58:07.271
There is one stop we have to make.

1230
01:58:10.449 --> 01:58:11.784
$400.000 at the back of the room.

1231
01:58:11.884 --> 01:58:14.216
The Stradivarius now at 400.000.

1232
01:58:14.253 --> 01:58:17.381
Against the telephone. 420.000.
450.000.

1233
01:58:17.423 --> 01:58:19.653
Against you. sir.
500.000.

1234
01:58:19.692 --> 01:58:23.355
500.000 back to the front.
500.000.500.000.

1235
01:58:23.396 --> 01:58:24.864
Wait here.
I'll just be a minute.

1236
01:58:24.964 --> 01:58:26.899
I might have to go around the block.

1237
01:58:26.999 --> 01:58:29.160
All right. if you have to.

1238
01:58:36.108 --> 01:58:39.202
1.100.000.
1.100.000.

1239
01:58:39.245 --> 01:58:40.546
1.200.000.

1240
01:58:40.646 --> 01:58:42.348
Is that a bid. sir?
Don't be shy.

1241
01:58:42.448 --> 01:58:44.717
All right then. I'll take it.
1.300.000.

1242
01:58:44.817 --> 01:58:46.552
1.400.000.

1243
01:58:46.652 --> 01:58:48.962
1.500.000.
Yes. sir. I've got you.

1244
01:58:48.988 --> 01:58:51.684
$1.600.000.
1.600.000.

1245
01:58:51.724 --> 01:58:54.488
Not you. sir?
1.650.000.

1246
01:58:54.527 --> 01:58:56.128
1.675.000.

1247
01:58:56.228 --> 01:58:58.364
- Not yours. ma'am.
- Mr. Morritz.

1248
01:58:58.464 --> 01:59:01.058
Please don't let me forget this.

1249
01:59:01.100 --> 01:59:03.969
Against the telephone now.
Against you. sir.

1250
01:59:04.069 --> 01:59:05.571
1.810.000.

1251
01:59:05.671 --> 01:59:10.233
1.850.000.
1.875.000 in the room.

1252
01:59:10.276 --> 01:59:11.977
1.900.000.

1253
01:59:12.077 --> 01:59:13.713
1.900.000.

1254
01:59:13.813 --> 01:59:16.043
1.900.000 on the telephone.

1255
01:59:16.081 --> 01:59:18.081
1.920.000 in the room.

1256
01:59:18.083 --> 01:59:19.985
1.920.000. I've got you. sir.
Thank you.

1257
01:59:20.085 --> 01:59:21.654
1.940.000.

1258
01:59:21.754 --> 01:59:24.746
Not yours. ma'am.
Neither of yours.

1259
01:59:24.790 --> 01:59:28.658
$1.940.000.

1260
01:59:28.694 --> 01:59:30.262
Son of a bitch.

1261
01:59:30.362 --> 01:59:31.797
I'll take 10.000.000.

1262
01:59:31.897 --> 01:59:34.161
You want back in. sir?

1263
01:59:34.200 --> 01:59:36.327
Is that a yes?
No.

1264
01:59:36.368 --> 01:59:39.565
The Stradivarius now at $1.940.000.

1265
01:59:39.605 --> 01:59:41.766
Not yours. ma'am.

1266
01:59:41.807 --> 01:59:45.641
Neither of yours.
$1.940.000.

1267
01:59:45.678 --> 01:59:47.079
Against you all in the room.

1268
01:59:47.179 --> 01:59:48.948
Is that all then?

1269
01:59:49.048 --> 01:59:51.107
Fair warning.

1270
01:59:51.150 --> 01:59:52.451
1.950.000 on my left.

1271
01:59:52.551 --> 01:59:56.681
Down to you two now.
1.950.000.

1272
01:59:56.722 --> 01:59:58.986
Not yours. sir?
Not yours. Paul?

1273
01:59:59.024 --> 02:00:01.024
The bid is 1.950.000.

1274
02:00:01.060 --> 02:00:03.262
- Did you clean this?
- Against you all in the room.

1275
02:00:03.362 --> 02:00:04.864
- Who's responsible for--
- The Stradivarius now

1276
02:00:04.964 --> 02:00:06.499
at 1.950.000.

1277
02:00:06.599 --> 02:00:08.667
- I have to get the last lot.
- All done then.

1278
02:00:08.767 --> 02:00:10.069
- I come to fix--
- Excuse me--

1279
02:00:10.169 --> 02:00:12.104
- --I asked the client--
- What's going on?

1280
02:00:12.204 --> 02:00:15.196
- We're gonna have to--
- $1.950.000.

1281
02:00:15.241 --> 02:00:17.971
And sold to the lady on my left.

1282
02:00:24.083 --> 02:00:26.519
The last sale of the evening.
lot number 72.

1283
02:00:26.619 --> 02:00:27.920
on the turntable there.

1284
02:00:28.020 --> 02:00:31.456
- Wait!
- The star of the night--

1285
02:00:31.490 --> 02:00:32.758
- The tag!
- The last violin

1286
02:00:32.858 --> 02:00:35.691
of Niccolò Bussotti. 1 681.
A master--

1287
02:00:35.728 --> 02:00:37.992
I put the tag on myself!

1288
02:00:38.030 --> 02:00:40.430
If she will give us the pleasure.

1289
02:00:40.466 --> 02:00:42.466
Too late.

1290
02:00:43.135 --> 02:00:45.399
Here she is now.
lot 72.

1291
02:00:45.437 --> 02:00:48.235
the so-called Red Violin.

1292
02:00:48.274 --> 02:00:49.775
- Here we go now.
- The last order bid--

1293
02:00:49.875 --> 02:00:52.469
Call security.

1294
02:00:52.511 --> 02:00:55.781
So. we'll open the floor
and who will start us off?

1295
02:00:55.881 --> 02:00:58.349
260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

1296
02:00:58.384 --> 02:01:00.252
270.000.
Suzanne on the telephone.

1297
02:01:00.352 --> 02:01:02.411
280.000.
Back to you. sir.

1298
02:01:02.454 --> 02:01:04.581
- Here.
- 300.000 in the back.

1299
02:01:04.623 --> 02:01:07.217
320.000.
I see you. Suzanne.

1300
02:01:07.259 --> 02:01:09.625
340.000.
340.000 now in the front.

1301
02:01:09.662 --> 02:01:12.790
400.000 at the back of the hall.
420.000.

1302
02:01:12.831 --> 02:01:16.096
500.000.500.000.
Against the telephone now.

1303
02:01:16.135 --> 02:01:17.069
- Suzanne--
- 500.000.

1304
02:01:17.169 --> 02:01:18.938
- stop it.
- Is that a yes? No?

1305
02:01:19.038 --> 02:01:20.873
Against you. sir.

1306
02:01:20.973 --> 02:01:23.464
600.000.
700.000.

1307
02:01:23.509 --> 02:01:25.977
Not yours. sir.
Not yours.

1308
02:01:26.011 --> 02:01:29.105
I have $800.000.

1309
02:01:29.148 --> 02:01:32.015
$900.000.

1310
02:01:32.051 --> 02:01:34.884
$1.000.000.
Mr. Ruselsky.

1311
02:01:34.920 --> 02:01:38.287
$1.100.000.
1.200.000.

1312
02:01:38.324 --> 02:01:40.986
Not you. sir?
Ma'am?

1313
02:01:41.026 --> 02:01:42.728
- 1.200.000.
- Are you sure?

1314
02:01:42.828 --> 02:01:45.160
1.300.000.
1.400.000.

1315
02:01:45.197 --> 02:01:46.999
1.400.000.

1316
02:01:47.099 --> 02:01:47.833
1.500.000.

1317
02:01:47.933 --> 02:01:50.163
1.600.000.

1318
02:01:54.506 --> 02:01:57.532
- Mr. Morritz.
- Down to you two now.

1319
02:01:57.576 --> 02:02:00.545
- 2.000.000. Mr. Ruselsky.
- Mr. Morritz!

1320
02:02:00.579 --> 02:02:03.605
- Mr. Morritz.
- 2.100.000.

